ad the whole book\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','2009-09-30','2009-10-13 05:50:36'),(494,90,'DAM','Ian makes deals\r\nhe doesn\'t want to give away his leads\r\nHe needs access to some positions\r\nWhat if he finds out who the #1 person is (the woman) and then cuts a deal with #2 to make her look bad\r\nHow does he do that? He doesn\'t know\r\nwhat does he trade; whatever it is, he should try to trade somethig else and then they suggest what they want\r\nhow about he goes to the woman and offers to help her cold call if she\'ll let him fill some of the positions in the company. she accepts and he does some work\r\none of the other associates asks him why he\'s helping \"that bitch\" \r\nHe tells him and this guy says that he would happily give some positions if he could only put her down a notch\r\n\r\nHow do you bring a person down a notch? You find matches for all the positions he\'s already matched. This means that the positions will take longer to fill and, perhaps, your candidates will get the position instead of his. \r\nThe rules of the company work like this:\r\n1) You have an assigned company. You can only place people there. You can\'t send a resume to a company you aren\'t assigned to\r\n2) You can get candidates from anywhere; that\'s up to you. \r\n3) The company DOES have some candidates that are created by global activities such as job fairs and buying them from other companies and hiring  firms to do cold calls\r\n4) You can trade your positions; that is, if I have positions in xyz corp I can let you fill them and take credit for me.\r\n5) When you fill a position -- when the company signs off -- you get credit for that. Your compensation is tied to this. \r\n\r\n','2009-10-02','2009-10-10 16:40:03'),(495,101,'davemenc',' ','2009-10-02','2009-10-02 21:10:02'),(496,101,'ALM&DAM','\r\n\r\n\r\nReply\r\n		\r\nForward\r\n		\r\n		\r\n \r\nReply\r\n \r\n|\r\namber morrison\r\n to dave\r\n	\r\nshow details Sep 10\r\n	\r\nTo be honest with you Rongo, 