thing back. Then, when they \"take advantage\" of me it doesn\'t surprise me because, well, they don\'t know any better (people don\'t know who & what they really are). But when they treat me with love back I am completely blown away and absolutely jazzed. Burning Man is amazing to me because I can open my heart and almost ALWAYS get love back. \r\n\r\n    I hope and pray that you will be able to open your heart without being hurt. I wish I could shield you from the pain but it\'s simply not possible. Remember that you are powerful and no one can hurt you without your participation. \r\n\r\n    One more thing. I really shouldn\'t give advice at all. My purpose isn\'t to tell people how to do stuff. I\'m here to help people through it when they get hurt by life. So feel free to ignore my advice as too difficult or dangerous.  \r\n\r\n    But you would do me tremendous honor and service if you think of me when you are in pain. You don\'t even have to tell me; just think of me and know I love you and it will help. Really.\r\n\r\n    Love \r\n\r\n    Dave / Rongo!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n    On Wed, Sep 9, 2009 at 10:08 PM, amber morrison <amberlynnmorrison@yahoo.com> wrote:\r\n\r\n        That, \"Suggestion,\" is a piece of wisdom in my eyes.  Thank you, and I will remind myself of your words.  \r\n\r\n        I admire and love you so much, as well.  I was telling Marcus about our magical playa experience that fell on Thurs night, and I basically summed up my personal experience with you as:\r\n                                   I fell in love with everyone here. But, on Thurs night, I deeply fell in love                                with Rongo.  He was so amazing, and he surprised me every second                                  with his magnificence.  \r\n        And that Rongo, only sums up my appreciation of you and your being.  Thank You.\r\n\r\n        Amber  \r\n\r\n\r\n        --- On Wed, 9/9/09, Dave Menconi <davemenc@gmail.com> wrote:\r\n\r\n\r\n            From: Da