d. Well, everyone but Fitz, maybe. He seemed to admire here and, anyway, he couldn\'t be bothered to kill someone, even if he had a reason. \r\n\r\nOne by one I talked to everyone in the club. \\\"Where were you?\\\" I asked again and again. \r\n','2011-03-25','2011-03-26 17:07:08'),(619,99,'','*** cop PETE interacted with allure and she just laughed at him. Big upset, stormed out \"this isn\'t over\" I\'ll get you kind of thing*** \r\n\r\nAlmost everyone is a suspect from Erica to the cop who allure blew off to Nick, the wackjob with the gun. \r\n\r\nBut Erica was at home (and could prove it, in case you\'re wondering) the wack job and the cop couldn\'t have gotten in the club and almost everyone else either had a solid alibi or didn\'t have a motive. \r\n\r\nEveryone but brandy and Viki. Brandy and Allure just seemed to hate each other at first sight and Viki believed that Allure ruined her marriage with Wil. I was particularly interested in Viki because she hadn\'t been around since the murder -- was she on the lam? \r\n\r\nAnd who showed up at my bar just as I was thinking about this but Viki. I asked her the question I asked everyone: \"Where were you the night Allure died?\" \r\n\"Fuck you pops. I didn\'t kill that bitch, as much as I would have liked to.\" She sat there looking stubborn. I waited. \r\n\r\n\"Well, if you must know, Wil and I went away to try to fix our marriage. I\'m not sorry she\'s dead because, if there was anything between Wil and her, it died with her. But were on vacation in the mountains the whole week. Just got back today. When I heard about Allure it was shocking. Go away for a few days and the place goes to hell!\"\r\n\r\nLater, I asked Brandy straight up. \"Where were you the night Allure died.\"\r\n\"Fuck you pops.\" Maybe I should have found a different way to task the question. She sipped her water for a bit, then, \"OK, Fine. I was here. I killed that skank and I\'m glad!\" She stomped off.\r\n\r\nI was stunned! Could it really be that easy?\r\n\r\nBefore I could think about what Brandy had said Huni came over with her friend xxx. \r\n\r\n\"Huni,\" I asked, \"Where were you the night Allure died?\" I expected her to say \"fuck you\" but she surprised me. \r\n\r\nShe looked over at her friend uncomfortably. \"Well, I, ah, I was with Michael Young,\" she stammered. \"All night\"  Her friend looked shocked. I would guess that she didn\'t know that Huni was sleeping with Young after hours.\r\n\r\nThis certainly put a different light on  things! Young definitely didn\'t do it. I was certain he was involved. And I would have pegged Brandy as your basic bully. Sure she might push someone or even hit them but she would never use more force than she needed to keep everyone afraid of her. Killing someone would certainly scare everyone but not if she did it in secret, late at night. Not if people didn\'t know she did it.\r\n\r\nMaybe it had been an accident. She had been there late with Allure and they got into a punching match and Allure went down the stairs. \r\n\r\nBut why would they be at the club together? Brandy hated Allure. Who takes a shower with her enemy last at night? What was up with that!?\r\n\r\nThe answers seemed to generate more questions. I needed to have a longer talk with Brandy. I called Erica on the radio. \"Have you seen Brandy?\" \r\n\r\n\"Brandy left. Something about a family emergency.\" \r\n\"Crap. Do we have any contact information on her?\"\r\n\"Yeah, I have a home phone number on the contact sheet, just like everyone else.\"\r\n\r\nI felt pretty dumb that I let Brandy just walk out of the club after she admitted to killing Allure but I had been kind of in shock. I had a lot of questions for her and I really wanted to talk to her. \r\n\r\nI limped up the aisle to the back door and went into Erica\'s office. It didn\'t take long to dig up her number and dial it. I knew it was a long shot but it was worth a try.\"\r\n\r\n\"Hello?\" a man\'s voice answered. \r\n\"I\'m looking for Brandy.\" \r\n\"Brandy ain\'t here. She\'s at work making money for me.\"\r\nThis seemed like a very odd answer to me. \"Are you her husband?\"\r\n\"Yeah, she\'s my slut wife. Like I said, she\'s out making money for me. Who are you?\"\r\n\r\n\"This is pops from the club she works at. She\'s just left for a family emergency but I need to talk to her as soon as possible.\"\r\n\r\n\"A family Emergency!? That bitch will have a family emergency! Her husband is going to send her to the emergency room if she skipped out on work!\"\r\n\r\nI was shocked by this reaction. It seemed our bully, the terror of Jack\'s Gentleman\'s Club, was married to an even bigger bully. And more even than a bully, almost an owner by the sound of him. I decided to tell him the whole story and see what he said. Maybe he\'s give her up. \r\n\r\n\"Brandy skipped out right after she told me that she killed Allure, the woman at the club who was killed last week. Do you know what she was ding in the club at 3 AM that night?\"\r\n\r\n\"Yeah, I heard about Allure but she sure as fuck wasn\'t in no club! She was her, entertaining me and my friends until almost 4 AM. She was pretty put out about it, too, on account of she had to work next day. Tough shit, I told her. Yeah it was quite a party!\"\r\n\r\n\"Do you ahve any idea why she would tell me she killed that woman?\"\r\n\r\n\"Oh hell, who can say why women do shit?\" He paused for a minute, considering. \"But she sure does love to terrorized the girls in that club. Maybe she figured if word got around that she killed a girl she\'d rule the roost! What a numbskull. She\'d go to jail long before anyone believed she killed someone! Maybe that\'s why she cut out. I\'m gonna kick her ass when she comes home!\" He laughed a nasty sort of laugh and hung up. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','2011-03-25','2011-03-26 21:46:06'),(620,99,'','With a lot of hard work I\'d gone from everyone being a suspect to no suspects at all. For the rest of the day I tried to think of what to do next. \r\n\r\nI figured that if I knew why she was here that night it might help. XXX had been banned from the club for working with Allure. Maybe she knew what was going on with Allure just before she died. \r\n','2011-03-26','2011-03-26 21:52:06'),(621,99,'','<h3>MACK</h3>\"You\'re going to need a survailance system. I bought you this one. It has two cameras and it all hooks into a VCR with an 8 hour loop. Best of all, it was really cheap!\" Michael Young\'s eyes were glowing as he gave the box to Erica with the air of a father giving a Christmas present to his favorite daughter. \r\n\r\nErica got on the radio \"Mack, come to Pop\'s bar, please\". A moment later Mack appeared from the lobby where he had been setting up his space. \"What\'s up?\" he asked and then he saw the box. His face fell. \"We\'re not going to install that junk here are we?\" he whined. \r\n\r\nYoung looked annoyed. \"Who\'s this kid? Erica, why do you insist on turning my club into an island of misfit toys?\" \r\n\r\nErica simply ignored him. \"Mack, I need you to put up these two cameras and set up the VCR in the front.\" \r\n\r\n\"Erica, this is the worst security system, ever! Two lousy cameras are too easy to avoid, an 8 hour loop is just crazy when it\'s easy and cheap to store the video continuously and it\'s a VCR, for god\'s sake! Can we please do something from THIS CENTURY?\"\r\n\r\n\"Listen kid,\" put in an annoyed Young, \"this is my club and I\'ll put up whatever surveylance I want. I don\'t know if you\'ve been paying attention but we\'re in a strip club. The customers don\'t feel good about being on tape. Just do what you\'re told.\"\r\n\r\n\"Ok but I could build a better system from spare parts than this could ever be.\" Mack wandered off, muttering to himself. \r\n\r\n\r\n','2011-04-06','2011-04-06 14:51:39'),(622,99,'','\"What are you studying\"\r\n\r\n\"Mark Twain\'s Huckleberry Finn. I had to write an essay about the book so I wrote about the way that what we do here in a strip club is just like what the Duke and the Earl did to the townspeople with their show \'Nonesuch\'. They claimed to present Shakespeare and then just ran around naked. We claim to provide love and sex but then, well, just run around naked. Somehow ours fools the customers while theirs just angered them but it really all comes down to the same thing.\"\r\n\r\nShe tapered off when she saw how I was staring at her. I didn\'t understand what she was talking about. I guess I never was much into literature. ','2011-04-06','2011-04-06 14:56:41'),(623,63,'DAM','<h3>Origin Myth</h3>\r\nSomewhere around the age of 50, I woke up. It was not a surprise. I\'d been desperately trying to shake the waking sleep that I had lived in all my life, indeed, that everyone lives with. \r\n\r\nI can\'t quite remember the exact moment but i know it happened right after I told my spiritual teacher that I wasn\'t his student anymore\r\n\r\nLord knows I\'d been asleep my whole life up to that point...\r\n\r\nMy father was an ex marine turned state law enforcemnt agent. Theing they say about marines is \"once a marine always a amarine\" and I can tell you it\'s true. My childhood was more like boot camp than what most children experience. But for all that I was never beaten. Abused emotionally, perhpas, but noever physically. \r\n\r\nThe youngets of six kis, I was always painfully sware of my ignornace and incapacties. Everyone one around me was smarter and stronger and faster and genererally more able than I. More importantly -- and more painfully for me -- everyon around me was elaborately uninterested in spending time with me. \r\n\r\nMy mother had been a nurse before she married my father and after my 5 siblings, she seemed annoyed to still be taking care of children. Oh, she was a good mother, I wasn\'t neglected or anything. But I was all too aware that I was more of a burden than a joy.\r\n\r\nSo I grew up loneyly and convince of my own lack of ability. Ihad an easy childhood, mind you -- no beatings, allways enough to eat and so forth -- but not a happy one. \r\n\r\nI want to a catholic grade school. By the secoind grade I was convinced of two things. First, I knew there was a god. But I also knew that He wasn\'t -- He couldn\'t be -- anything like what the nuns described Him to be. According to them he was testing us all the time and if we passed -- all the time, every test, our whole life -- we would go to heaven. but if we failed the test -- and it was governed by a complex and elaborate set of rules -- we would spend the rest of eternity in endless unimaginable torment. \r\n\r\nHow this description could apply to a God who loved me and knew everything they would not explain. Much later I realized that the \"god\" they described acted exactly like a Catholic Nun -- endless testing with any slightest failure rewarded with punishment. \r\n\r\nWhen it came time for confirmation (the first Holy Sacrament that a child has any choice about) the Catholic Church and I parted ways, at least metaphorically. In reality, I went on to 4 years of Catholic high school. As a freshman the ancient Jesuit priest who was my counselor insisted that I should get confirmed but I knew that he couldn\'t make me do it so I didn\'t even bother to disagree. \r\n\r\nThus twelve years of Catholic schooling came to a close with and all I knew was that there must be a God. For a time I thought Christian groups could help me find my way but they seemed to believe that all you needed to know was that Jesus Christ is your Savior. I was looking for a somewhat more nuanced theology.\r\n\r\nSo I gave up. For at least 5 years, I believed in God but did nothing in support of that faith. \r\n\r\nThen I met Earl Rice who would be my Sp ritual Teacher for the next 20 years and I joined The Church for Unity and Service. The story of the Church for US is an interesting and instructive story but it is not my story so it will have to wait. \r\n\r\nFor my part I approached my spiritual learning from the point of view that I was broken and needed to be fixed. I went to all the classes and all the retreats and to every service. When the Spiritual Head of the Church suggested that people only had beards because they were trying to hide, I shaved off my beard (my wife later told me that she cried). \r\n','2011-04-27','2011-04-28 00:55:43'),(624,63,'DAM','It seems there is an important or, at least, ubiquitous, theme in my life: the universe has been gentle with me but has never let me get comfortable.\r\n\r\nGentleness has made me sensitive -- I have not become either distrustful of other nor guarded in my feelings. Discomfort has made me sympathetic -- I may not have experienced the depth of another\'s anguish but I probably have experienced the kind of anguish they have. \r\n','2011-05-02','2011-06-28 21:30:30'),(625,99,'','Inteview Questions\r\nwhat is your ideal solution/resolution?\r\nWhy do you care about this issue?\r\n\r\nWhere did you go to college?\r\nDo you have any other special training that has prepared you to be a better teacher (list)?\r\n\r\nCould you give some personal background (single/married, children, etc.)?\r\n\r\nAre you involved in any community organizations (charities, church, etc.)?\r\n\r\nWhat are your hobbies?\r\n\r\nWhere did you grow up?\r\n\r\nAre there any political or social issues you feel passionately about?\r\n\r\nDo you have a nickname?\r\n\r\nWhere have you traveled?\r\nWhat are your greatest stresses and what causes you the most anxiety?\r\nWhat\'s the hardest thing for you \r\n\r\nWhat\'s your most vivid or disturbing recurring dream?\r\nWhat song do you get stuck in your head the most often?\r\nDo you sing in the car or other times when you\'re alone? What kind of music? How good are you?\r\nFavorite weekend activity.\r\nWhat\'s your favorite funny story about yourself?\r\nName one thing about yourself that most people don\'t know.\r\nList three misconceptions that people often have about you 