7:12'),(113,22,'Issues',NULL,0,113,0,'2005-06-15 05:57:12'),(114,22,'Future Enhancements',NULL,0,114,0,'2005-06-15 05:57:12'),(115,23,'Introduction','<P>The purpose of this site is to allow people to ask for opponents in games that they want to play. Other people will sign up for the games. When the game is filled the original requestor (\"coordinator\") is sent an email with the email addresses and names of all the players who are interested. He must then find a time and a place where they can all play.\r\n<P>For example, a coordinator fills out a game form requesting players for a particular board game with a particular number of players. For example, a 7 player Diplomacy game. He specifies whether he\'s going to play, the city he\'d like to play in and anything special about this game. Then people wanting to play Diplomacy and willing to go to that city sign up. When there are 7 players signed up, a list of the players is sent to the coordinator and the game is closed out. If no one signs up for the game then it\'s closed after 3 months. ',0,20,0,'2005-07-23 08:03:51'),(116,23,'Definitions','<ul><li>Coordinator -- an individual who sets up a game\r\n<li>Player -- an individual who signs up for a game\r\n<li>Visitor -- an individual who looks at the site\r\n<li>Game -- a game that has been registered\r\n</ul>',0,40,0,'2005-07-23 08:11:09'),(117,23,'Database Design','',0,60,0,'2005-07-23 09:00:46'),(118,23,'Technical Design Notes','',0,80,0,'2005-07-23 08:03:51'),(119,23,'Issues','',0,100,0,'2005-07-23 08:03:51'),(120,23,'Future Enhancements','<ul>\r\n<li>adding scheduling to the site so the coordinator doesn\'t have to schedule\r\n</ul>',0,120,0,'2005-07-23 09:01:29'),(129,13,'test again','<P>Whatchamall is an online mall. Individuals and companies who want to sell \r\nthings on the internet will buy space in the mall, paying a modest monthly \r\nfee, and receiving a simple interface that allows them to manage their \r\ninventory, manage their payment methods, and