INSERT INTO `games` VALUES (1,'Puerto Rico',' Rio Grande / Alea',90,'Economics','','',7,'Keep',2,'Dave',0,'',273,300,'','http://www.boardgamegeek.com/game/3076',2,6,6,NULL,1,'2010-04-11 04:37:27'),(84,'Lord of The Fries','CheapAss Games',60,'Other','Card','Brainless',1,'Gone',1,'Unknown',0,'',218,134,'','',3,8,6,NULL,5,'2010-06-03 15:16:33'),(3,'Merchant of Venus','Avalon Hill',180,'Science Fiction','Trading','Thinky',4,'Keep',2,'Dave',0,'',195,96,'','',1,6,6,NULL,1,'2010-04-11 04:50:37'),(4,'Modern Art','Mayfair',60,'Art','Trading','Easy',2,'Keep',2,'Dave',0,'',194,95,'','http://www.boardgamegeek.com/game/118',3,5,5,NULL,1,'2010-04-11 04:37:27'),(5,'Vinci','',150,'Civilization Building','','',7,'Keep',2,'Dave',0,'Richard Garfield',290,325,'<P><I>RoboRally</i> has a deck of cards that represent moves for you robot -- turn left, turn right, move back, move forward and so forth. You secretly select a set of moves for your robot as do your opponents and then everyone goes through them move by move. Robots can bump each other during the move and, if they end a move facing another robot may shoot at the opponent. <P>The board over which the robots move is complicated and dangerous, with conveyor belts, traps and pits scattered throughout.  The goal is to be the first to move through the checkpoints (selected before the game) and complete the race. Along the way, it\'s possible to pick up special cards that allow all manner of special abilities. <P>The game has 8 pewter figures of robots. We\'ve painted ours elaborately and put felt on the bottom (to protect the board). ','<h3>Other Interesting Links</h3><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.boardgamegeek.com/viewitem.php3?gameid=18\"> Game Geek Comments </a></ul>',0,6,0,NULL,1,'2010-04-11 04:37:27'),(83,'Ticket To Ride','',45,'','','',7,'Gone',1,'Unknown',0,'',83,0,'','',0,0,0,NULL,0,'2010-06-03 15:16:33'),(7,'Chaos Marauders','',45,'','','',7,'Keep',2,'Dave',0,'',7,0,'','',0,4,0,NULL,1,'2010-04-11 04:37:27'),(10,'Mississippi Queen','Rio Grande Games',45,'Riverboat','Tiled Race','Moderate',3,'Keep',2,'Dave',0,'',272,296,'','http://www.boardgamegeek.com/game/256',1,6,6,NULL,1,'2010-04-11 04:37:27'),(11,'I\'m The Boss','',60,'','','',7,'Gone',1,'Unknown',0,'',11,0,'','',0,6,0,NULL,16,'2010-06-03 15:16:33'),(12,'Basari','',45,'','','',7,'Keep',2,'Dave',0,'',12,0,'','',0,4,0,NULL,1,'2010-04-11 04:37:27'),(27,'Zendo','',60,'','','',7,'',5,'Unknown',0,'',27,0,'','',0,10,0,NULL,0,'2010-04-11 04:36:21'),(85,'Dead Wood','',45,'','','',7,'',5,'Scott',0,'',85,0,'','',0,0,0,NULL,0,'2010-04-11 04:36:21'),(15,'Munchkin','',15,'','','',7,'Keep',2,'Keith',0,'',297,337,'','',0,6,0,NULL,1,'2010-04-11 04:50:37'),(88,'IceTowers','',10,'','','',7,'',5,'Unknown',0,'',88,0,'','',0,0,0,NULL,0,'2010-04-11 04:36:21'),(89,'Niagra','',60,'','','',7,'',5,'Adony',0,'',89,0,'','',0,0,0,NULL,1,'2010-04-11 04:37:28'),(20,'Union Pacific','',90,'Railroads','','',7,'Keep',2,'Dave',0,'',301,342,'','',0,0,0,NULL,1,'2010-04-11 04:37:27'),(21,'Samarkand','',30,'Trading','','',7,'Keep',2,'Dave',0,'',276,306,'','',0,0,0,NULL,1,'2010-04-11 04:37:27'),(86,'99','',60,'','','',7,'Gone',1,'Unknown',0,'',86,0,'','',0,3,0,NULL,0,'2010-06-03 15:16:33'),(23,'Fluxx','',5,'Abstract','Card','Brainless',1,'Keep',2,'Dave',0,'',212,128,'','http://www.boardgamegeek.com/game/258',2,6,6,NULL,1,'2010-04-11 04:37:27'),(24,'Democrazy','',45,'','','',7,'Gone',1,'Unknown',0,'',24,0,'','',0,10,0,NULL,0,'2010-06-03 15:16:33'),(25,'Bohnanza','	Rio Grande Games',45,'Farming','Card','Easy',2,'Keep',2,'Dave',0,'Uwe Rosenberg',25,268,'','http://www.boardgamegeek.com/game/11',2,7,6,NULL,1,'2010-04-11 04:37:27'),(26,'Bang!','',30,'Westerns','Card','Moderate',3,'Gone',1,'Unknown',0,'',26,265,'','http://www.boardgamegeek.com/game/3955',4,7,7,NULL,8,'2010-06-03 15:16:33'),(28,'Fight The Power','',15,'','','',7,'',5,'Scott',0,'',28,0,'','',0,10,0,NULL,0,'2010-04-11 04:36:21'),(29,'Cattle Baron','',45,'Other','Other','Brainless',1,'Keep',2,'Dave',0,'',29,127,'','http://www.menconi.com/games/cattlebaron.html',2,8,6,NULL,1,'2010-04-11 04:37:27'),(30,'Mag-Blast','',60,'','','',7,'Gone',1,'Unknown',0,'',30,0,'','',0,8,0,NULL,0,'2010-06-03 15:16:33'),(31,'Stratego','Milton Bradley',45,'War Game','Tactical Sim','Thinky',4,'Gone',1,'Unknown',1961,'',134,3,'<P>This is a strategic game in which the players secretly arrange their armies. During the game, you don\'t know which of your opponent\'s pieces are which.  The idea is to find and capture your opponent\'s flag while preventing him from doing the same. Much of the strategy is in the set up but there is also a great deal of depth to the game play -- good game play can make up for poor set up. <P>The game has a simple hierarchy to it. You have lots of Scouts which lose to everything, fewer Miners who can only take Scouts, fewer Sergeants who can take only Scouts and Miners and so on up to your single Marshal who can take anything. Add to this simple arrangement, Bombs, which blow up anything that touch them except Miners (who can defuse them) and the Spy who can take the Marshal if he can strike first (which creates some interesting games of cat-and-mouse) and, of course, the Flag which loses you the game. <P>From the box:<P>\"The gameboard is your battlefield. You have an army of men at your disposal and six bombs. Your mission--protect your flag and capture your opponent\'s flag.<P>\"Secretly place your men, bombs and flag on the gameboard with these objectives in mind. But remember your opponent is doing the same thing, so you must plan a defense as well as an offense.<P>\"Once the armies are in place, advance your men. When you\'re one space away from an enemy, attack. You and your opponent declare ranks. The lower-ranking man is captured and out of play.<P>\"You control your pieces and risk your men in battles where the strength of your enemy is unknown. The suspense builds as your men move deeper into enemy territory. Move with caution and courage. The next piece you attack could be a bomb. And when attacked, it could \"blast\" your man off the board and out of play.<P>\"The first to capture an enemy flag is the winner!\"<P>The edges of the box have broken and been fixed with strapping tape. The box is also fairly worn (with some tearing along the edges) but still in reasonable shape. The map is in much better shape but has letters and numbers marked around the edge and down the middle (at the dawn of CB radios my friend up the street and I used to play a game every morning before school). Unlike newer versions of the game, this one has enameled wooden pieces instead of the plastic pieces of later games. All in all this game is in very good shape considering it is copyright 1961 (29 years is a while). Even without this consideration I give it a \"good\" rating because it is still quite playable and the damage to the box  and markings on the board do not affect the aesthetic enjoyment of the game. The map has letters and numbers written on it (we used to play it by CB when I was young). <P>This game is somewhat old and there have been newer editions since it came out. But the newer editions have plastic pieces that aren\'t as nice and, well, I think it\'s better to have an earlier version, provided it\'s still playable. ','',2,2,2,NULL,0,'2010-04-11 04:36:21'),(32,'San Juan','',45,'','','',7,'',5,'Unknown',0,'',32,0,'','',0,4,0,NULL,0,'2010-04-11 04:36:21'),(90,'Bitin\' Off Hedz','CheapAss Games',60,'Other','Other','Brainless',1,'Keep',2,'Dave',1996,'James Ernest',90,132,'Players move their dinosaurs down the track toward extinction. At various points they have an opportunity to throw rocks at each other to slow down the winning dinosaur. And, of course, if you land in a square with another dinosaur you can bite off his head and send him back to the beginning. The game can take a while. ','http://www.boardgamegeek.com/boardgame/1527',2,8,8,NULL,1,'2010-04-11 04:37:28'),(36,'Give Me the Brain','',30,'','','',7,'Keep',2,'Dave',0,'',36,0,'',''