INSERT INTO `mantis_bug_text_table` VALUES (1,'All messages, when you attempt to read them, appear to be just the first message','Login as dave/pass\r\nClick on any message on the main screen or on the recent list\r\nIt should come up as the actual message\r\nBut it comes up as the first post, don\'t know why',''),(2,'When you select a category, you get multiple first post articles listed instead of the real list of articles.','Log in as dave/pass\r\nSelect a category (any category)\r\nThere will be some number of posts which will all say \"first post x\" and all be in the general category \r\nIt should have different posts with the correct names\r\n','The number of displayed articles (all with \"first post x\", of course) varies but the reported number is always 23.'),(3,'I know there are articles in the system but they don\'t show up. \r\n\r\n','goto ...bmachine/admin.php\r\nLogin in as admin \r\non the admin screen there will be no articles\r\nverify that there ARE articles in teh system by logining in as any user (dave/pass)\r\nYou SHOULD see everything as admin','At a guess, I\'d say that one of the selects I hacked is used by the admin to bang in the '),(4,'As it currently works, if the user has an admin cookie set it won\'t even set a user cookie. But if he doesn\'t have a user cookie set then it may not let him see anything unless the admin priv bits are set.\r\n\r\nThe admin can see anything in the admin screen which is as it should be. But in the normal place he\'s just another user and he can\'t change users. \r\n\r\nOf course, he can go in and give himself read and write privs for everythign. Or he can go into the admin page to read and write stuff. But he doesn\'t get a user cookie.\r\n\r\n','','We could fix this a few different ways\r\n1) we could hack the 11 different select codes (and I\'ve already done this in one place) so that the admin user (user 0) is special. \r\n2) we could leave it the way it is\r\n3) we could allow the admin user to also set other cookies for other users\r\n\r\nI think that we\'re going to have to hack this into the 11 selects but I don\'t see that it\'s a very urgent problem since there are multiple workarounds.'),(5,'The fact that admin is special in getPostList but not in other article selection routines means that he will see messages in odd places. \r\n\r\nObviously he can easiily work around this by simply going into the admin.php page to read the posts or by removing his cookkie and entering a user cookie or by setting the priv flags in admin. So I don\'t see this a huge problem.\r\n\r\nBut it\'s kind of odd and will probably get us into trouble eventually. ','',''),(6,'see summary','run bmachine/admin.php\r\nenter admin password\r\ngo to authors\r\ntry to edit an author',''),(7,'When you set the private bit the category disapears ','',''),(8,'When you edit an author\'s privs you are supposed to see two rows of check boxes and you do. But there is supposed to be a header above them identifying one as \"read\" and one as \"write\".\r\n','',''),(9,'I ran update on the blog database and I lost all the privacy bits. it would be nice if didn\'t do this kind of thing.','',''),(10,'See sumary and str','use mysql to identify some private articles in a public category\r\nlog in as admin\r\ngoto admin home\r\nnotice that you can\'t see the articles\r\nyou should be able to see everything as the admin\r\n',''),(11,'see summary','',''),(12,'No post was wound with the id 27 !\r\n\r\nShould be \"No post was found with the id 27 !\"\r\n','',''),(13,'When you click on the back and forward buttons on the top of the calendar they don\'t seem to work. I\'m not sure they ever worked but I think it\'s pretty likely I broke them.','',''),(14,'PrivAuthorized must be called and we must doctor the cat','',''),(15,'select * from bmc_cats,bmc_write where author=$author and bmc_write.cat=bmc_cats.id;','',''),(16,'Currently there are two write data routines one for admin and one for priv. The only difference is that the priv one goes back to main while the admin goes back to admin. That should be generizable. ','',''),(17,'Currently there are two sets of post code, one for priv and one for admin. They may not be at all different except about the categories that are shown. Try to set it up so that we only have one. ','',''),(18,'The existing priv authorized has 2 specialized db functions between the comment that describes the function and the function itself.\r\n\r\nAlso it is build on the assumption that we have to open the database with a unique link for each access. we now know this to be untrue. \r\n\r\nRewrite the file so it\'s cleaner and merely does unique queries from the database, using the same link (which I assume will be faster.','',''),(19,'select * from bmc_write where auth=7;\r\nonly put the link if the select finds at least one row ','',''),(20,'This one is fairly simple. Duplicate the post page from the admin post page but only allow the author to post to categories he\'s allowed in. If he\'s not allowed in any categories, generate and error and go back. \r\n\r\nselect * from bmc_write,bmc_cats where bmc_write.auth=2 and bmc_write.cat=bmc_cats.id;\r\n\r\nOh, and this implies a link on the home page that allows him to post a message which should only be there if he has at least one record in the write table. \r\nselect * from bmc_write where bmc_write.auth=2;\r\n','',''),(21,'In category add, if you put a tick in the title it will cause an error because mysql sees the tick in its special character form. (You will note that Im not putting ticks in this message for the same reason -- it\'s not just bmachine). \r\n\r\nWe need to add stuff that either removes or escapes the ticks. \r\n','',''),(22,'when you set the write check mark, it automatically sets the read bit\r\nread the file before you write it and see what the write bit used to be.\r\n\r\nIn the case where the write bit is not set in the file but where it\'s set in the form, set the read bit. but if the write bit is currently set in the file but the read is not set in the form, reset the read bit.\r\n','',''),(23,'Currently (under the current design) only people who can read articles can edit them, but we\'d like people to be able to edit their own article even if they can\'t read it.\r\n\r\nHow the hell do you do that?','',''),(24,'This is probably found in the inc/profiles directory','',''),(25,'admin (only) can select a specific theme for a category\r\nwhenever a message from that category is viewed that theme comes up','',''),(26,'When you edit a message the format keeps switching to text from html; surely it would be better if it stayed the same as what it was. Only change it if the user does. ','',''),(27,'When you post a message it allows you to supply a user name. If you have a cookie that says who you are it should either default to that or out and out prevent you from using anything else.','',''),(28,'<h2>Phase Two Changes</h2>\r\n<P>In phase two the admin will be able to allow certain users to see certain articles. In the edit author screen, we\'ll add a list of all the categories with checkboxes next to them (checked or not according to the author\'s current privs) and we\'ll save that data when the save button is clicked. \r\n<P>Also, when a category or a user is deleted we\'ll remove all the flag associate with that category or user. ','',''),(29,'This means that you\'ll have to change all the places where it checks for an admin password and make it authorize and then make sure it\'s the admin. \r\n\r\nAlso you\'ll have to fix the code so that it puts the config.php admin password into the database. \r\n','',''),(30,'When you read a post you should be able to edit that post if \r\nyou are the author. So we need a conditional link at the top or bottom of the post display page.','',''),(31,'WHen you\'re posting a new message as a non-admin, the logout link at the top has no apparent effect.','',''),(32,'There should be a conditional link, next to the New Post and Login links that will allow non-admin users to logout. Maybe it just calls the admin logout function and deletes all cookies. Or maybe we need a different function becuase the admin logout returns you to the admin login screen...\r\n','',''),(33,'The author selection the non-admin post is menu form element but non-admins can select one and only one item. So you have a menu with just one author in it. Not sure if it can be fixed or not. ','',''),(34,'This isn\'t used anywhere anymore and so should be removed.','',''),(35,'I\'ve got the bMachine permissions version running at:\r\n\r\nhttp://classic2.church-for-us.com/bm/index.php\r\n\r\nWhen I enter using that URL, I see the public categories, \"Public Stuff\" and \"General.\"\r\n\r\nI have two users, \"Admin\" with password \"pass,\" and \"Earl\" with password \"password.\"\r\n\r\nHistorically, I started them with no access boxes clicked, and they could see nothing. I then granted them access to more categories and, as I added access, they could view more categories.\r\n\r\nI then removed access, but the categories still display.\r\n\r\nAs the site now stands, neither author has any permission to view or edit anything, and the checkboxes show that in the Admin panel, but all the categories display when they log in.\r\n\r\nI clear cookies before each entry.\r\n\r\nMaybe this is irrelevant with the new revision, and maybe I\'ve screwed something up.\r\n\r\nI have not modified any files except the templates in the theme set. (You can go back to \"pure stock\" by selecting the default theme in the Admin panel.)\r\n\r\nI set all file permissions to \"777\" for testing.\r\n','',''),(36,'Running in menconi.com/bmachine I entered the admin password. I can\'t see ANY categories OR posts. I looked in the database (based on teh config.php file) and there ARE both posts and categories there. ','',''),(37,'http://67.113.154.163/bmachine/index.php?id=35\r\nThis is a test of editing messages\r\nPosted by greenhornet / Category :: General\r\nPosted on Sep 03th (Fri) 2004\r\n\r\nClick on the title and it tries to find message 10 even tho this is message 10.\r\n','',''),(38,'The code that connects to edit takes you to the admin edit code and it wants you to enter an admin password. \r\n\r\nProbably has code that checks to see if you\'re logged in as the admin. When I find that code I\'m golden.','',''),(39,'Currently, an individual message can be made private in which case it can\'t be seen by the public even if it\'s in a public folder. Private messages can be seen by any author, regardless of his privileges. \r\n\r\nSince we can have private categories which are selectively shown to people with certain privs we can eliminate the private message flag. \r\n\r\nTo remove this, we remove the field from the database and then remove every single reference to it. Esentially any select that has \"private\" in it and that is dealing with posts (not categories) should be fixed.','',''),(40,'It just shows a blank screen...','',''),(41,'When mode=admin is encountered, add a login field and post a cookie (session duration)\r\nIn Most Places:\r\nadd, edit (directory name) and delete directories, logout (as admin)\r\nAdd: create a directory of the required name into the correct spot and then add default contents\r\ndelete: just remove the directory\r\nedit images: the images in the non-leaf nodes are backgrounds in the table and there are buttons in the corner that allow you to upaload a new one\r\nyou can alos edit info_array.php (but you can\'t do this at the root node)\r\n\r\n\r\nIn Leaf Nodes\r\nThere is a product array. This cannot be edited directly\r\nReplace image, edit description, add item, delete item, logout (as admin)\r\nAdd item is at the top and allows you to upload a new image; it\'s given a default description and you can edit the description normally\r\nReplace image, edit description and delete item are in the middle of the page.\r\nReplace image allows an image with the same name to be uploaded to the same place\r\nedit description allows you to edit that one description\r\ndelete item simply removes the picture\r\nlogout: delete cookie and re-enter system\r\nAll these things have to recreate the product_array \r\n','',''),(42,'When mode=admin is encountered and there is no cookie, add a login field and post a cookie (session duration)\r\n\r\nThis implies that there should be a password stored somewhere\r\n','',''),(43,'In all non-leaf directories, allow admin users (with an admin cookie) to  create a directory of the required name into the correct spot and then add default contents.\r\n\r\nThere should be a special default directory with the default contents (maybe derived from the parent or sibling directory).\r\n','',''),(44,'Admin users (authenticated by cookie) can edit a directory name. We need a link to this code. When you select a directory to edit you we then accept a directory name and change that direcory to that name.\r\n\r\nBe sure to check the new name for validity no bad characters, reasonable length, etc.','',''),(45,'Allow admin users (authenticated by cookies containing the password) to delete directories. Allow them to select a directory from a list and then just remove the directory\r\n','',''),(46,'edit images: the images in the non-leaf nodes are backgrounds in the table and there are buttons in the corner that allow you to upload a new one\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIn Leaf Nodes\r\nThere is a product array. This cannot be edited directly\r\nReplace image, edit description, add item, delete item, logout (as admin)\r\nAdd item is at the top and allows you to upload a new image; it\'s given a default description and you can edit the description normally\r\nReplace image, edit description and delete item are in the middle of the page.\r\nReplace image allows an image with the same name to be uploaded to the same place\r\nedit description allows you to edit that one description\r\ndelete item simply removes the picture\r\nlogout: delete cookie and re-enter system\r\nAll these things have to recreate the product_array \r\n','',''),(47,'you can also edit info_array.php (but you can\'t do this at the root node)\r\n\r\nJust read in the data in the file and put it in an editable field. On submit, use the code in index.php to write it back out. ','',''),(48,'The replace image link is in the middle of the page and it allows an image with the same name to be uploaded to the same place\r\n','',''),(49,'edit description allows you to edit that one description\r\ndelete item simply removes the picture\r\n','',''),(50,'Adding an item involves uploading a new picture and recreating the product array; the user can then edit the description.','',''),(51,'delete item simply removes the picture and recreates the product_array \r\n','',''),(52,'just delete the cookie and re-enter system\r\n','',''),(53,'Edit description\r\nadd login \r\nedit description','',''),(54,'maybe from the cookie?','',''),(55,'There are currently 2 submodes withind admin mode. The first is edit_desc, the second is new_description. Since these are written as separate modes, you don\'t have to ever have been in admin mode to execute them.\r\n\r\nOne solution is to check for the admin cookie in each of these cases. \r\n\r\nA better (IMHO) solution would be to make these modes sub-modes and to not even check for them unless the user is in admin mode, either because he said so (which would trigger a request for a password) or because he has a cookie. This would ensure that you can\'t be in a submod unless you\'re in admin mode. \r\n\r\nAll the places that say \"mode=*\" should be changed to \"mode=admin&submod=*\"\r\n\r\nAnd the code under admin should be changed to check for submodes ($PARAMS[\'submode\']) and rearranged so that admin is always checked first and, unless found, nothing else works. \r\n\r\n','',''),(56,'Currently the text is to the right of the picture.\r\n\r\nWhen the picture is short and the text is long it looks ugly because the space underneath the picture has no text. This is particularly bad when the picture is wide and squat (although now all pictures are the same width so maybe it doesn\'t matter so much).\r\n\r\nwhen the picture is long, however, this looks fine. \r\n\r\nIt might be nice to be able to move some of the text into a special field that\'s always below the picture. \r\n\r\nThere\'s \"promo text\" and \"linkage text\" which are currently unused and might be used as \"extended descriptions\"','',''),(57,'The admin should be able to hide an image or a directory.\r\n\r\nFiles with a leading underbar (\"_\") are hidden from view. And when the \"hide\" option is selected the entity it\'s selected for has an underbar prepended to it. ','',''),(58,'All the gallery pix on ebay are exactly 96x72 which means that it will distort unless it\'s set to something with that ratio. That\'s 1-1/3:1 \r\nSo set it to 1333 wide and then cut it off at 1000.','',''),(59,'IN the auction it has two place where shipping estimate comes up and a few places where the shipping estimate is used. \r\n\r\nFirst there is the \"SHipping and handling:\" spot at the top which should say \"Local Pickup Only\". \r\n\r\nThen there is the policy section bullet points which should say \"Buyer to pick up item in South Bay area (Milpitas).\"\r\n\r\nWHen we send out the invoice and when we\'re calculating what it all cost us, we use the shipping estimate field. \r\n\r\nWe need another field that either says \"Pickup Only\" or says the shipping estimate depending on whether the estimate is 0 or not. \r\n\r\nAlso the invoices would be different. We ask for an address but we should TELL our address. ','',''),(60,'This is a parent bug.\r\nFirst off, we need to fix the admin problems. \r\n\r\nWe need to add submddes as outlined in 55.\r\nWe need to add logout as outlined in 52. \r\nWe need to consider 54 and either do it or close it.\r\nwe need to move the password per 62.','',''),(61,'When the admin hides something it\'s hidden from other users but not from the admin. There has to be something on the screen that tells the admn that this object is hidden as well as something that allows him to \"unhide\" it. ','',''),(62,'It\'s currently coded into index.php but it should be int he config file','',''),(63,'currently there is a subroutine for writing the product array but it\'s not used every where. ','',''),(64,'OOPS! I put the logout link next to every image instead of at the top of the page. Need to fix that eventually but maybe it\'s not a very high priority. ','',''),(65,'Currently the code checks for images that aren\'t in the product array (by comparing the catalog array with the product array) but it does not check for images that no longer exist. \r\n\r\nThis will be a requirement for the admin delete function but I see no reason why code somewhere shouldn\'t compare catalog and product and remove from product anything that isn\'t in catalog. Then, if changes were made, write out product. \r\n\r\nIf we do this every time you can delete stuff by hand and it will all just work!','',''),(66,'I want to add a \"come look at it\" option (instead of Buy it). In this case, I need to own the code that sends the email. \r\n\r\nRewrite it in PHP and put it on the server (no huge deal). \r\n\r\nThis is called \"Garage sale\"','',''),(67,'This is for things that are local pick up. Buyers should be able to come look and then buy if they want. It\'s assumed that they will want to dicker but they came all this way...','',''),(68,'We want to add the following features\r\nHide pictures (61)\r\nReveal hidden pictures (57)\r\nReplace pictures (48)\r\nDelete pictures (51)\r\nFix logout position (64)\r\nDetect New Pictures (65)','',''),(69,'I just found a delicious bug! \r\n\r\nWhen you add an image that has a name that shows up in the directory after \"footer\" or \"header\" (not quite sure which), it\'s placed in the $jpg_list after these two file names (which are always there). Then these are removed when $jpg_list is copied to $image_list which leaves a gap. So now we have (for example) [1][2][4][5][6] in the array. This array gets passed to smarty and smarty looks at the first N. So it never gets to [5][6].\r\n\r\nActually, I think you\'ll see some of them since you\'ll only lose the 2 that were in the location of footer and header. \r\n\r\nWe didn\'t see this problem before because all the image names were capatilized which came, alphabetically, BEFORE the lower case. \r\n\r\nI think the way to fix this is to resort $catalog_array so that the gaps are removed but I have to see. ','',''),(70,'The list of the privs for an author show up in 3 columns. The first should say \"cat\" over it, the other two should say \"R\" and \"W\" over them so you can know what privs you\'re giving out.\r\n\r\n','',''),(71,'Currently the year is a text entry and it should be a pulldown. \r\n\r\nLook a the database and see what the years are. Eliminate the oldest year (the display will show the current year and the previous year so you can ever select the oldest year). ','',''),(72,'Currently the display was pulled right out of the spreadsheet which has an \"income\" section but simply has the sub-section headers for the expenses. The income and expense headers should probably be fancier -- bold or italic or larger or with a different background.\r\n','',''),(73,'The display should show both this year and the year before. It should show this in two columns and it should also show it on the graphs. \r\n\r\n','',''),(74,'Between the income graph and the expense graph should be a graph that shows total expense vs total income. Just two bars, just the totals. ','',''),(75,'Call it \"contributions\"? Maybe something shorter.\r\nShould have \r\nName tinytext,\r\nyear int\r\nJan decimal (9,2),\r\nFeb  decimal (9,2),\r\nMar decimal (9,2),\r\nApr decimal (9,2),\r\nMay decimal (9,2),\r\nJun decimal (9,2),\r\nJul decimal (9,2),\r\nAug decimal (9,2),\r\nSep decimal (9,2),\r\nDec decimal (9,2),\r\nstamp timestamp\r\nIf possible name/year is the unary index.\r\n\r\n','',''),(76,'Simple table: \r\nName tinytext,\r\nDate date (some date type),\r\npledge decimal (9,2),\r\ntimestamp\r\n\r\n','',''),(77,'Top of page has form\r\nname, pledge and add button; this adds (or updates) records to the database\r\nRest of the page shows what is in the database now:\r\nLeft side has a graph. Top one is total Income, second one is total expense. Rest are name and pledge amounts. \r\n\r\nWhen an add or update is done, after it adds or updates the record it recalculates the total yearly pledges (total pledges from the pledge database for the year times 12 for the total for the year) and puts that into the pledges income frield in the budget table. \r\nThen it recalculates the income and expense values and redisplays them. ','',''),(78,'we need the graph type to persist from run to run so we should add a hidden variable everywhere that says \r\ngraphtype=2&action=setgraph\r\nexcept we have to remove the check for action and just make it so that if graphytype is there we use it ','',''),(79,'\"Exceptional Pledges\" -> Donations\r\n\"Offertory & Donations\" -> Offertory\r\nRemove GSF\r\nThe changes should be guided by the new excel spreadsheet.\r\n','',''),(80,'Currently there are four tables laid out like this:\r\n1 2\r\n3 4\r\nWhere 1 is the revenue numbers, 2 is the revenue chart, 3 is the expense numbers and 4 is the expense chart\r\n\r\nChange the structure to \r\n1 2\r\nWhere on is the numbers and 2 are the charts. ','',''),(81,'The totals chart is  currently between the expense and revenue charts. It should be moved to the top of the page on the right. Test.php has an example placement of this','',''),(82,'The data in the database is based on an old spreadsheet and needs to be changed.\r\n\r\n','',''),(83,'We want one more graph, below the totals graph, that shows overall position for the year.\r\n\r\nThe title at the top will be \"Net Operating Gain/Loss\" where we say \"gain\" if the value is negative and \"loss\" if it\'s positive. \r\n\r\nThe title on the right should say \"Surplus\" or \"Shortfall\" but the actual value should be the absolute value. ','',''),(84,'DOn\'t know why but sometimes it pulls items in a ring. ','',''),(85,'Vexing. If you try any other address it will either convet it to 67.113.154.163 or it won\'t work at all.','',''),(86,'Need a program that will allow the adnminstator to add, delete and edit applications in the sytem. \r\n\r\nAdding would allow the entry of a name and description and would generate an application word and an application number. ','',''),(87,'A program that allows the admin to add, delete and edit users. Add an edit would include\r\nUsername \r\npassword\r\nadd and delete for applications, add shows the ones he doesn\'t have and delete shows the ones he does have.\r\nYou can add or delete one application at time\r\n','',''),(88,'we want the system to log every login attempt\r\nwe want as much information as possible about where the person was coming from\r\nhis user name\r\nhis password\r\nhis ip address\r\nthe date and time\r\nwhether he was successful\r\n','',''),(89,'we want to be able to generate reports based on the login logging data that might include:\r\n+ how many times a specific ip address has failed, \r\n+ how many times each user id has been tried \r\n+ how often certain people have logged in, \r\n+ how often certain applications have been used\r\n+ which people are using which applications\r\n','',''),(90,'It asks for a username and password, you give it and it and it tells you all the different applications you can go to and it hides all those you can\'t go to. It should be an App0 so that you can certainly go to THIS application. We probably want a login routine that will tell us, for a given user, all the applcation numbers he can go to. Ultimately, we want to limit the exposure of the database to people so we\'d like only the login program to have access to the user table. If we have the program return application names and descriptions, as well, then we can limit the exposure of the application table as well.\r\nPerhaps this whole system should be part of the login program. \r\n','',''),(91,'Currently the application field in the user table is list of application numbers. This isn\'t 1NF. WE need a separate table that has application and user numbers in it. Then we need to change all the other functions to get information from this table instead of just parsing the list.','',''),(92,'Currently, every application has it\'s own cookie. We only REALLY need the cookies for authentication. \r\nChange the system so that the ONE cookie it has contains  username, the date and a list of apps plus a hash that contains the username, the date a universal magic word and the lsit of apps. ','',''),(93,'Currently, ever application you go to will force you to log in again. WE need a way to only log in once and still be able to use all the applications that you want.\r\n\r\nThe direct way to do this is to check to see if there exists ANY cookie with your login information and, if so, validate that information and generate a new cookie. \r\n\r\nThe better way is to have only one cookie with all the information in it. Then you can either store the application data in the cookie or go back and look it up each time. \r\n\r\nStoring it in the cookie might be bad because it will tell people what\'s going on. ','',''),(94,'I think that if I simply change the URL to be https:// it will encrypt the message passed around by the system! 100 times more secure.','',''),(95,'The main thing is to allow them to change their password. Also lost password support (not sure how to handle that).\r\n\r\n','',''),(96,'DOn\'t know why but sometimes it pulls items in a ring. ','',''),(97,'Current we\'re just throwing stuff out in the order we put it in. If we sort the que by from field it will look better. ','',''),(98,'Current we\'re just throwing stuff out in the order we put it in. If we sort the que by from field it will look better. ','',''),(99,'printed items need to be dealt with','',''),(100,'Once we have separate functions for finding special symbols, we should call them and do the right thing with the info.','',''),(101,'When we save the data we do\'t output all the symbols. We need to. ','',''),(102,'Out put the symbols when showing the rings so that we can incorporate this into the maps. ','',''),(103,'When a tenant registers, he must select store type right up front so we know what categories to present him with. ','',''),(104,'Tentant registration has no validation at all. At an absolute minimum, we need to make sure that the user name is unique. We should also make sure that they actually entered the rest of the information and that the zip code is valid and so on and so forth. \r\n\r\nSo there needs to be an optional string that we pass to the Display_TenantRegistration routine that we put at the top of the form. \r\n\r\nAlso, we have to change the form so that it can accept values for all the fields - specifically the values you filled in last time. ','',''),(105,'There should be a Paypal link on the tenant registration page that connects to the paypal sandbox.','',''),(106,'Currently, a temporary password works forever. It\'s supposed to expire at some point (hence the accolade \"temporary\"). \r\n\r\nEarl\'s design calls for it to expire some hours after it\'s set but perhaps we should simply reset it the next time the password is reset, thus keeping it around until you can change your real password to something you remember. ','',''),(107,'We need two new fields to be added to the item table: RFID (radio frequency identification) and UPS (universal price code). Naturally, we will need to allow tenants to set and change both of these values. Both can be tinytext fields (thus avoiding any problem with the rounding of very large numbers). ','',''),(108,'If you install the databse using th