tion date of cookies on the assumption that the browser will not. It also reinstates cookies every time you do something that requires them. \r\n\r\nIt\'s not clear how to fix this. What does it mean to have login cookies that expire at the end of the session? Why would you do that? Because you want to make it easier on your customers? Perhaps a very, very long expiration would be better. \r\n\r\nShould the login system allow them to persist forever? It certainly can\'t know whether the browser has shut down since the last time it saw the cookie... '),(417,'If the user is using the system but he\'s not using any features that require authorization, shouldn\'t we keep his cookies fresh? At the very least, there should be the option to do so. \r\n\r\nThis would require a function that does nothing but refresh the cookie if the cookie hasn\'t expired. If you put it in every function then if the user does ANYTHING the cookie life gets extended. \r\nThis function doesn\'t need to be called if the user is doing something requiring authorization but it doesn\'t hurt so you can put it at the top of all the routines. ','',''),(418,'move loc_login code to library and include that file with the company list code\r\nThen hook in loc_GetAuth to the appropriate routines','',''),(419,'And call it help','','Lots of things have changed since I wrote that but lots have stayed the same. '),(420,'We\'d like it to take you whereever you were going and that\'s what it SHOULD be doing, as far as I know. ','',''),(421,'Strictly speaking, this is a login problem. But the company list needs logins and login really doesn\'t work without this. ','','I\'m thinking we should add it to the login scree; maybe the left hand side has login while the right side has registration. \r\n\r\nThen we need to catch it somewhere. '),(422,'For a long list, as you click on next repeatedly, it takes longer and longer!','',''),(423,'If you set it to have a page size of 25 and then you count there will be 26 on the page.','','This causes other problems. For example if you do next repeatedly, it will run out of things to display before it gets to the end so it will remove Next and Last but won\'t be on the last page listed!'),(424,'Two pages before the end, the next link disappears','',''),(425,'The Logout link doesn\'t seem to remove the cookie (which is it\'s purpose in life). ','',''),(426,'currently there is lots of whitespace on the page but not much description. it would be good to trade some of that white space for more description','',''),(427,'There is now way to block or delete a user','',''),(428,'This is kind of ironic but by adding a few features, local login could maintain a central database and can be a locally controled but centrally administered system.\r\n\r\n','','1) Add a routine that\'s called from the user that handles all events. No longer will the host application have to handle \"new user\" and other events for the login system.\r\n2) Create a central database with a privs list. Each application has a number and each user has a list of application number he can use. The difference is that you add or delete application privs from the application rather from a central location. QUESTION: if I try to register from two different apps how does it know that I\'m the same user. This is a major flaw.\r\nThe alternative is to simply have a field in the user database that says which app this user is for and then use uname/app as the key -- it\'s perfectly legal to have several different daves. \r\n'),(429,'Currently a user on todo can get to all products. I really want a user for EACH product','',''),(430,'TASK has \r\n\r\n    * id\r\n    * title\r\n    * duration\r\n    * assigned to\r\n    * start date\r\n    * desc\r\n    * project\r\n    * plus what\'s in the todo list table ','',''),(431,'TASKSTATUS \r\n\r\n    * entryid\r\n    * taskid\r\n    * currentdate\r\n    * hours worked this week\r\n    * OT hours this week\r\n    * hours to completion ','',''),(432,'comments \r\n\r\n    * commentid\r\n    * designid\r\n    * userid','',''),(433,'Users add\r\n\r\n    * efficiency (ratio of projected duration to actual duration)\r\n    * SD (standard deviation)','',''),(434,'The Project report should include the following stats (thse are all defined below)  \r\n  * Project total hours (projected)\r\n    * Percent Project Complete\r\n    * Project end date (projected with current data)\r\n    * Original start and end date\r\n    * BCWS\r\n    * ACWP\r\n    * Earned Value (BCWP)\r\n    * Schedule Variance\r\n    * Cost Variance\r\n    * SPI\r\n    * CPI\r\n    * EAC\r\n    * A list of all completed tasks showing how much longer they took than estimated\r\n    * A list of all developers, showing how far off their estimates were ','','    *  Budgeted Cost for Work Scheduled (BCWS) - the budgets for all activities planned to be completed. Total projected project cost based on work breakdown and resource costs.\r\n    * Actual Cost of Work Performed (ACWP) - the real costs of the work charged against the completed activities. ACWP = work completed (by measurement)\r\n    * Budgeted Cost of Work Performed (BCWP) or Earned Value (EV) - the planned costs of the work allocated to the completed activities. This is the Earned Value. Earned Value = Percentage project complete X Project Budget \r\n\r\n\r\nvariances\r\n\r\nSchedule and cost variances can both be calculated in monetary terms from the\r\ndata needed to produce the S-curves.\r\n\r\n    * Schedule variance is the difference between the Earned Value and the planned budget. SV = BCWP - BCWS\r\n    * Cost Variance is the difference between the Earned Value and the actual costs of the works. CV = BCWP - ACWP \r\n\r\n\r\nPerformance Indices\r\n\r\n\r\nSchedule Performance Index and Cost Performance Index give indications of the\r\nhealth of the project. Is the project on time, in budget or what?\r\n\r\n    * Schedule Performance Index is a ratio of Earned Value and the planned value of completed works. A SPI < 1 is not good SPI = BCWP / BCWS\r\n    * Cost Performance Index is a ratio of Earned Value and the actual costs of completed works. A CPI < 1 is not good CPI = BCWP / ACWP \r\n\r\n\r\nEstimate At Completion\r\n\r\n\r\nThe EAC gives an idea of the final costs of a project. It takes into account\r\nthe original budget (BAC), the Earned Value and the Cost Performance Index of\r\nthe already completed works.\r\nEAC = ACWP + ((BAC - BCWP)/CPI)'),(435,'For each task we want to know\r\n# Gathers, for every task, every week, hours spent this week, hours projected to completion (or % complete at the option of the user). To calculate %complete, take the total hours spent plus the hours to completion and divide into total hours spent and then multiply by 100.\r\n# Entry has an \"entry Date\" which defaults to today but can be changed to any date past or future\r\n# Entry is for the week of the date entered. If multiple entries are made for that week then only the last entrie (based on the time stamp) is counted -- he who writes last, writes best. ','',''),(436,'create a new directory and put both sets of code there, changing the name\r\nof the todo list and combining config files','',''),(437,'create a db with the appropriate tables','',''),(438,'instead of having an independent \"product\" list, make it get it\'s \"product\" data from the design project list','',''),(439,'I don\'t want to change the code but change everything the user can see.','',''),(440,'these are just like the existing \"formal\" document but are distinct','',''),(441,'Comments can be made to anything -- every task, every note, every section of every piece of documentation. They are dated, have an author value and can be deleted by the owner of the entity that are comments to. ','',''),(442,'add fields to todo list for owner, duration; I think there is another entry for this.','',''),(443,'these are things like holding you to one project, doing auto ordering and so forth','',''),(444,'so you can get data in from excel spreadsheets','',''),(445,'so you can export to project','',''),(446,'add a field to todo items\r\n\"Milestone number\" and if this is 0 then this item is a milestone. All other\r\ntodo items must be associated with a milestone. ','','Todo lists must be associated with special todo items called \"Milestones\". \r\n\r\nThe easiest way to do this in the database is to add a field to todo items\r\n\"Milestone number\" and if this is 0 then this item is a milestone. All other\r\ntodo items must be associated with a milestone. \r\n\r\nFrom a UI perspective, you just get a list of all the milestones in the project\r\nand allow one to associate a todo item with one of the milestones. At any\r\nfuture date a todo item or milestone can be associate with a milestone in the\r\nedit process.  If a milestone is associated with a milestone it and all the\r\ntodo items that pointed to it are now associated with the new milestone.\r\n\r\nThe implications of having todos associated with a milestone is that the\r\npredicted completion date of the milestone is calculated from the durations of\r\nthe todos and it is not complete until all the todos are complete.\r\n\r\nAn ugly aspect of this system is that we have to calculate the todos of\r\ndifferent actors separately. The easiest way to calculate the projected end\r\ndate  for a milestone is to consider all the todos of one resource (aka\r\n\"actor\") and add up all their remaining time. Convert this into a calendar date\r\n(8 hrs/day, 40 hrs/ week added to today\'s date) and you have the projected date\r\nwhen that actor will be done. Now do that for all the actors. Take the latest\r\none and that\'s when the milestone will be done. While we\'re at it we might as\r\nwell allow one to see which resource is the \"critical path resource\" -- that is\r\nthe one with the longest duration.'),(447,'There needs to be two lists of tasks. One is filtered by project and the other is filtered by user. The list of projects is the same and the detail of the task can be the same.\r\n\r\nThe default is to show the projects that the user is associated with and then show only those tasks he is the developer on. \r\n\r\nWe also need to let him see the entire list of projects and ALL the tasks for that project. \r\n\r\nAnd, perhaps, all the users and then all the tasks for any one of them. \r\n\r\n','',''),(448,'need a user file, need an admin app, perhaps need links','',''),(449,'in the create todo item form','',''),(450,'The todolist table should store the NUMBER of the product. The relevance here is that the todo list can\'t be converted until this is fixed. ','',''),(451,'No error, mind you; it just doesn\'t work','',''),(452,'You have an error in your SQL syntax near \'order by name\' at line 1','',''),(453,'Over time, for no known reason, each user\'s privs seem to replicate. Because the priv list has no master number it\'s not clear what you\'re actually doing when you delete one. \r\n\r\nAnyway, the system still works but it\'s hard to administer when every user has a dozen copies of each of their privs!','',''),(454,'IF the user has no privs it tells him that it\'s an invalid variable in foreach on line 105 in authenticate.php. ','',''),(455,'You have the option of entering tasks for any project but the milestones are from all the tasks (the current situation) or their from one specific project.','','The obvious solution is to insist that tasks are associate with the project that you were looking at when you jumped to add task. We don\'t need to select a project and the milestone is from the list for THIS project. '),(456,'it has a form for each milestone instead of having one form for ALL milestones. it looks stupid','','the problem is that this page is generated by 3 different routines and some of the processing needs to be moved up'),(457,'Essentially, when new effort left and effort completed records are received, we need to make sure they are correctly updated. \r\n\r\nI think this works but...','',''),(458,'the current project list uses random vales for total effort; clearly calculating it would be better! :)','',''),(459,'effort remaining is current a random number\r\n\r\nThe effort remaining is the last task status record. ','',''),(460,'This is the ability to related sub tasks to super tasks. RJ calls this \"outlining\" \r\n\r\nAll that we need to do is to add a place to specify the parent of a task. We need to add this spot to every enter and edit task. \r\n\r\nWE need to add a column for \"parent\" to the task list and update that.\r\n\r\nWe need to have all the display stuff use that. ','',''),(461,'This goes along with the one that adds it to the database. (460?)\r\n','',''),(462,'Now that we can track, add and edit subtasks, we need to calcualate their effort and effort remaining. Essentially, we calculate the total for each of these for all the subtasks. \r\n\r\nAnd, while we\'re on the subject, do it for milestones, too. ','',''),(463,'Task list primarily but there are probably others. ','',''),(464,'this is kind of large but it\'s very important','',''),(465,'we wrote libraries for some of this; add them in\r\n\r\nMainly transaction logging but I really like the databases update stuff, too. ','',''),(466,'It has to be on a secure server to work correctly.','',''),(467,'the last step...','',''),(468,'If you check the done on one task, all the tasks get their done bits set!','',''),(469,'The basic idea here is to add a priority to each project. \r\nThe obvious global priority of a task is then all the tasks of the highest priority project are higher in priority than the next higest priority project. \r\nThe next idea is to add a due date for each project and an (optional)duration for each task. Then the \"date priority\" for each project is the due date minus all the durations (i.e. latest start) where the one with the earliest latest start is the highest priority.\r\nFinally, you could mix these two idea by taking the number of days from now to the latest start for a project and adding it to the priority of the project. ','',''),(470,'5 types of users (just create the 5 types for now; no capabilities yet)\r\n   1) Worker (can see and edit his own stuff, create projects, add himself to any project, mark tasks done, etc)\r\n   2) Manager (has a defined set of workers; can add or remove his workers from any project; can look at an edit any information about any of his workers; can see reports about any of his workers)\r\n   3) Project manager (has a defined set of projects; can add or remove any workers from/to any of his projects, can edit any of his projects, can see reports about any of his projects)\r\n   4) Sr. Manager (can see everything, look at any reports, but edit nothing)\r\n   5) Admin (can see everything, edit everything, see every report, no exceptions)\r\n   Note that a single person can have several overlapping roles (ich). Managers are often project managers as well. ','',''),(471,'Changes send email to owners (admin, manager, project manager)\r\nPeople should be allowed to subscribe/unsubscribe to this feature.','',''),(472,'Allow only Admins and PMs  to add, delete & edit projects (adding: anyone, delete and edit: admins and PMs; creating a project requires you to define a PM)','',''),(473,'Limit ability to add, edit and delete tasks to pm and admins','',''),(474,'Limit ability to add, edit and delete workers to admins.','',''),(475,'Limit ability to edit people\'s privs and add new people (only admins)','',''),(476,'The first report we want to have is one that reports, for every milestone in a project, when it is expected to be done, based on the current information. \r\n\r\nThis is the most basic calculation, adding up all the durations for each resource, converting this to calendar dates and then picking the latest calendar date as the date. ','',''),(477,'We want to be able to have tasks that are like the old todo list -- just a task with a priority. With this addition one could just use this as the todo list system and not get all sweaty about project management. We want the system to allow you to mix todo items and tasks in the same project. \r\n\r\nThe simplest way to do this is to allow one to add tasks with no duration. Another way is to have a special category or milestone called \"todo\" which collects tasks that aren\'t actually part of the project duration. \r\n\r\nAnd, while we\'re at it, add a thing called \"future\" which is things that aren\'t in this release but will be in a future release. ','',''),(478,'I can log in to look at the list but I can\'t log in to add items','','I tested this on the church iMac. This may be an edge case.'),(479,'One fault of this system is that it doesn\'t have a master list: what is it I\'m supposed to do next? \r\n\r\nYou should be able to click on any item and have it be added to the master list. Then you should be able to change the priorities of items WITHIN the master list to be different from their priorities on the normal lists. \r\n\r\nThus, if it\'s time to do project FOO I can do the items from FOO but if I want to put some of the items from FOO onto the master list so that I can do them at other times, then I should be able. \r\n\r\nNOTE: this is just another way to handle a problem I\'ve been working on for a while: how to have one unified list? This is just my latest solution but I like it more than the others. ','','This should be quite straight forward. A table \"mastertodo\" could have a todo item id and a priority (along with the other, standard, fields). When an item is added to the master todo, the item number is added and the priority from it\'s old list is filled into the priority field in the master list. \r\n\r\nThere should be a page that displays only master list items. \r\n\r\nThen when you check it off from the master list the actual item is marked as done and it\'s done everywhere. \r\n\r\nYou may or may not want to remove done items from the master list. As long as you should the master list page with the proper selection (perhaps you only want to show the items that aren\'t done yet) then it doesn\'t really affect how the system works. \r\n\r\nI would take the current page that displays todos and use that as the form for the master list. \r\n\r\nIf you create a task to be on the master list, what \"product\" is it associated with? '),(480,'I\'ve been having trouble with the login system where it wasn\'t correctly reporting the username and so design doesn\'t show the correct set of designs. \r\n\r\nI think it\'s because there is a call to loc_getusername() that either has a parameter (it should\'t) or is called getusername(). The quickest way to find this is to delete getusername() from loc_login. ','','I want to create a login.php that has all the functions in loc_login.php with the loc_ removed. Then you include_once login.php in loc_login and we can happily track down and destroy loc_ without having everything break all at once. '),(481,'The actual problem is that the design app is calling the wrong thing but that\'s because the loc_login.php is really just a temporary hack. ','',''),(482,'The link on the name of the project goes to information ABOUT the project. But I almost always click on it thinking I will get to the notes on the project. \r\n\r\nAlthough the way it is now is logical, the way I actually use it makes it wrong. I should add a link to the right that says \"about\" that links to the page about the project and change the link on the name to notes section.','',''),(483,'Write a front page that authenticates, allows for registration, and displays -- what? \r\nWelcome to redwall, list of games on the system, an ad and a link to the redwall general forum','',''),(484,'We need some forum software. Redwall itself will have a forum plus each game gets at least one forum. ','',''),(485,'The guessing game needs an introduction page. Describes the game, links to the rules, has a list of running games with links to their public and private pages. ','',''),(486,'The control function is run by a crontab, opens up the database and looks for games that need to be run. \r\n\r\nIt needs to be reentrant and it needs to not be painfully slow. Preferably, it needs to run the game turn as a separate process (if that can be done safely). ','',''),(487,'There is a table that controls what games get run when (through the control function). We need a page that edits that information. It can add games, delete games and modify games. ','',''),(488,'We need to be able to pass xml to run guess','',''),(489,'There needs to be a function that tells numbers game to stop a game and clean up after itself. ','',''),(490,'we need a sit manager that can edit users, and track what games are on the site. It should also be able to create new instances of games and close out old ones. \r\n\r\nTHis is like the control editor and probably will be a superset of it\'s functionality but it also controls the SITE.\r\n\r\n','','WHen you set up a new game it has to have a directory allocated for it, it has to have a forum, a marketing page, rules, an entry on the front page that connects all this.\r\n\r\nWHen you set up an instance of a game, it has to have a forum, a entry page (which might have public information or might just fall through to the user page), have pages for the users, '),(491,'we need to read and generate xml\r\nwe also need a schema for the various parts of the system. Some games aren\'t going to need all of the things that other games need so it needs to be flexible and extensible. ','',''),(492,'We want to have application and roles built into the system.\r\nRight now we have admin but there is no facility to check to see if you are allowed to use THIS application or what you might be allowed to see WITHIN this application (ROLES). I would like to add this facility','',''),(493,'At http://www.turnstylegames.org/numbers/index.php the \"register link\" is linked to http://www.turnstylegames.org/numbers/index.php?mode=register\r\n\r\nWhat I want it to do is to take you to the login page (or, better, a page that only has registration), and allow you to register. It doesn\'t always do that (in fact, I can\'t seem to get it to ever do that). ','','This one is not critical but it\'s probably the same problem with the other two. And it\'s fairly important. '),(494,'On page http://www.turnstylegames.org/numbers/index.php the link \"login\" doesn\'t seem to take you to the login page, even if you are not logged in.\r\n\r\nThe current location of the \"login\" link is http://www.turnstylegames.org/numbers/index.php?mode=login','',''),(495,'The link from the main numbers page to game 2 doesn\'t seem to work right. It takes you to a game one page (with the apparently wrong url) and then you aren\'t logged in and it doesn\'t know who you are!\r\n\r\nNOTE: this is only true if you aren\'t logged in\r\n\r\nMaybe we need a reload?','','This is huge because a player will try to go to a page, log in and then get crap on the page. It makes the user experience essentially unusable, even tho he could just reload and it would work. SO CLOSE...'),(496,'The main page doesn\'t have a help link. ','',''),(497,'The help file wording for the \"cheating\" section is probably not sufficient. It needs to be made clear that we\'re not talking about playing in multiple GAMES but multiple accounts in the SAME game. ','',''),(498,'On the page http://www.turnstylegames.org/numbers/index.php?mode=guess&gameno=1\r\nthe \"help\" link goes to \r\nhttp://www.meissen.org/redwall/numbersgamerules.html\r\nWhen it should go to \r\nOn the page http://www.turnstylegames.org/numbers/numbersgamerules.html','',''),(499,'the game 1 and game 2 links on the \r\nhttp://www.turnstylegames.org/numbers/index.php?mode=guess&gameno=1\r\npage shouldn\'t really be there. ','',''),(500,'http://www.turnstylegames.org/numbers/index.php?mode=guess&gameno=1\r\nThere should be a link to the main marketing page from the game page (above)','',''),(501,'On the page http://www.turnstylegames.org/numbers/index.php?mode=guess&gameno=1\r\nIt says:\r\nGame # 1 | Round # 80 | Round ends: Daily\r\nThat\'s probably not what we want. \"Daily\" should probably be the NAME of the game and I\'m not sure we want to give a number.\r\n\r\n','',''),(502,'On http://www.turnstylegames.org/numbers/index.php?mode=guess&gameno=1\r\nthe text\r\nGame 1 ends at Midnight; Game 2 at Noon\r\nshould be removed','',''),(503,'Put a link at the top of the page to the main page','',''),(504,'The numbers game forum link doesn\'t really link anywhere','',''),(505,'The forum link really doesn\'t belong on the guess page','',''),(506,'The time stamps are being added as \"0000-00-00\" instead of as the date. This probably means we\'re doing it wrong, maybe because we\'re actually setting it from the field in the form. ','',''),(507,'The table name is itbpaf not ITBPAF. ','',''),(508,'In theory, when you start there should be no itattorney already in existence so you shouldn\'t have to drop the table before you create it but in practice it\'s likely the the tester has already created it and may have failed to drop it again so it doesn\'t hurt to drop it and it may help.','',''),(509,'at the bottom of most pages there is a copyright notice; this should be removed from all pages. ','',''),(510,'The attorneys in the bpaf page (it/index.php?mode=d_bpaf) (or attorneyno values in the itbpaf table) should be none zero and there should be some attorneys in the attorney page (/it/index.php?mode=d_atty) (or records in the itattorney file).\r\n\r\nIn fact, after the scripts are run, all the values in the attorneyno field in the itbpaf table are 0, all the fields in the attorney column of the bpaf page are blank, the itattorney table has no records and the attorney list page reports that it has no records. \r\n\r\n \r\n','','Since this may well be a mysql version problem here is the result of running mysql -V on my system. \r\nmysql  Ver 14.12 Distrib 5.0.48, for redhat-linux-gnu (i686) using readline 5.0\r\n'),(511,'Upper and lower case are significant on this server (because it\'s unix? some specific setting?)','',''),(512,'according to the spec, the effective start should default to the start date','',''),(513,'On page 4, of version 1.2 of the data validation document, section 2.1.1 field number 9 \"Effective Start\" is described as \"mandatory and greater than start date\". This is incorrect.\r\nThe statement about the default value is correct -- this field defaults to \"start date\". Given that it default to the start date it doesn\'t have to be greater than. Since the system will enter it for the user if it\'s blank this field is not mandatory (in the sense that the user can leave it blank). ','',''),(514,'According to the spec effective end should default to end date; instead the field is required to be entered.','',''),(515,'version 1.2 of the validation spec, page 4, 2.1.1, field 10 \"Effective end\" is said to be mandatory. \r\nBut if the user doesn\'t enter it, it defaults to the end date so it\'s not mandatory. ','',''),(516,'You can\'t change the amount field (which is correct, ref 2.1.1.4) but if you try to save the record without entering it (which is impossible, note) it gives you an error. ','','it/index.php?mode=a_bpaf'),(517,'This is a process problem. The amount is defined as the total of all the project amounts. The spendable is defined as the amount. But you must save a record to enter a project amount and you can\'t save a record without entering an amount. \r\n\r\nDepending on how the logic works, this may not be a problem but it can\'t work how the documentation says it works. ','',''),(518,'This will only take a minute and really doesn\'t require any other work (you don\'t have to enter the data). It may not add great value but it\'s cheap and it could be useful. \r\n\r\nI don\'t think the phone number should be required. \r\n\r\nThis is, of course, a change (feature) not a bug. ','',''),(519,'In the email field of the add attorney field, it\'s not clear exactly what format is required for the email. a@b.c doesn\'t work but a@bc.d DOES work. \r\n\r\nA little string that says what is expected would be helpful. \r\nit/index.php?mode=a_atty\r\n\r\n','','As an aside, I\'m not sure we need to validate this. '),(520,'I don\'t see any reason that the email in the attorney field is required. It\'s kind of nice to have it there but not at all essential. ','',''),(521,'The prefix field is supposed to default to the 1st 3 letters of the company name. But when you start you haven\'t entered the company name so it starts blank. If you try to skip it, you get an error but then if you enter a company name, it is updated appropriately.\r\n\r\nIt should not give you an error when it\'s left blank until you actually try to submit the page (in which case, the system will have filled it in). \r\n\r\nI think this field should be moved to the bottom so that the user STARTS by putting the company name in and then the prefix just gets handled. ','',''),(522,'The webmaster link links to webmaster@menconi.com which is probably not what we want. We we probably want is an email address defined somewhere accessable so that it can be easily changed. \r\n\r\nProbably putting it in a file somewhere would be good enough; maybe the config. php file? ','',''),(523,'On many pages there are two lines that say:\r\nVersion:\r\nLast changed on .\r\n\r\nI think we should remove the version and last changed lines from the pages. ','',''),(524,'Currently the $ is above the amount field and it should be to the left. ','',''),(525,'If a bpaf record has no bpafrefno (perhaps it was entered before the verification code was written), how does it get a bparfrefNo? ','','Seems like the admin could be tasked with fixing this one.'),(526,'There also seem to be some sorting/navigation issues.  It seems that when you click on the heading that you\'d like the 4 page list of BPAFs to be sorted by (like \"date\" or \"spendable\") the page you are looking at gets sorted but if you click \"Next page\" or click on a page number, the page it takes you to is not in sequence with the sorting data.   It goes back to alphabetical (I think) (or the xth page of the default sorting method)','','I haven\'t reproed this one yet; it was reported by one of the users who are poking at it to see what it will be like. '),(527,'In the edit bpaf page 0.00 is not accepted as vaid money. Zero IS a valid value in this field because we often have BPAFs for things that cost money but don\'t allow us to spend any money -- this is, in fact, the main reason for a \"spendable\" field, to allow us to have a contract that\'s worth money to the company but that doesn\'t add any money to our \"buckets\".','',''),(528,'If the next step start date is bad, you can\'t edit the bpaf. This is fairly minor because the user can just add some date. But it seems like this should be auto-generated, anyway, so if it\'s a bad date of the form 0000-00-00 (which is the majority of cases) it should be changed to the date of the last time this field was changed or the last time the record was changed or, worst case, todays date. ','',''),(529,'When the bpaf is created an attorney has not been assigned so it\'s not possible to enter which attorney the bpaf has. One solution is to allow a special value of \"not assigned\". This should be the default.\r\n\r\nThis is a minor severity because an easy work around -- add an attorney named \"not assigned\". ','',''),(530,'I really don\'t like the fact that the links have nothing to indicate that they are links. There are a variety of places where it\'s not clear what\'s going on because of this. ','','The standard blue text with underline would actually be my preference (what can I say, I\'m a traditionalist) but there may be some ways to differentiate links that fit with whatever our scheme will be when we get to that. '),(531,'If you have 90 lines in the page, the page links are 1234 (which is correct). If you hit next 2 times you should now be looking at the 3rd page and it should still show a \"next\" and a \"last\" link but it doesn\'t. ','','Note that this is a bug in the library I forced you to use. Sorry about that and all that. But the good news is that you can change it in any way you see fit; we don\'t have to give it back or use it anywhere else.'),(532,'If you enter 0 into the amount field in the budget page it doesn\'t allow it because it says it\'s not a valid money. \r\n\r\n0 is a valid amount in this context because many projects have no budget. ','',''),(533,'One time, when I check availability for an unavailable prefix, I got dialog box that said \"undefined\" and did not get an answer about the availability of the prefix. ','',''),(534,'The \"Company Page\" sounds like a page with a list of companies while \"Company Summary Page\" sounds like a page that has summary information for a company. Since this is the latter rather than the former, it should be called \"Company Summary Page\". ','',''),(535,'The finished and pending bpaf pages should have some kind of title.','',''),(536,'Each of the records in the pending and finished bpaf pages need to have have a link to edit the record. ','',''),(537,'It seems impossible to set the page size, the filter, or to sort by any field. ','',''),(538,'The add page doesn\'t work at all; no add, no verify. No errors.','',''),(539,'Passwords should be encrypted in the system. This also implies that the we need a \"change password\" function somewhere. ','',''),(540,'If the invoice were sent electronically it\'s perfectly legal for them to be the same. We just can\'t see how the received can be BEFORE the sent.','',''),(541,'BPAF Ref list showed not only the BPAFRef# but also the project (1st project is probably OK)\r\nif there are more than one project it could have an asterisk.','',''),(542,'bpaf list showed not only the BPAFRef# but also the project (1st project is probably OK)\r\nif there are more than one project it could have an asterisk.','',''),(543,'when trying to add an invoice it would be very nice to see in the bpafref list which bpaf has money','',''),(544,'when entering an invoice add a button to search for a BPAF with sufficient budget for the specified project. ','',''),(545,'    Expired BPAFs donâ€™t affect the budget, even if invoices were applied against that BPAF while it was active.  So in my case, I put in all of my old BPAFs and all of my old invoices, and those old invoices are reducing the money available out of the active BPAFs.  I had to go change the effective end dates to all be in the future.','','> You seem to know about assigning bpafref to invoices. Are you using the\r\n> newest version of Susana\'s invoice tracker -- it should just work\r\n> correctly. We may have some kind of disconnect here.\r\n\r\nYes, I am.  The problem is that if a BPAF has expired, it no longer shows as being part of the budget for the product and any invoices that were from the time that the BPAF was valid come out of the new lower available budget.  Let me give and example:\r\n\r\n1. Let\'s say we have 2 BPAFs for DTE.  One is $50K for 1/1/08 - 5/30/08 and the other is for $100K for 6/1/08 - 12/1/08.  Total budget showing today will be $150K.\r\n2. Now let\'s say that each month we put in an invoice for $10K. You will see the available budget decline to $140K, 130K, etc.\r\n3. On 6/1, the first BPAF expires.  Suddenly DTE will show as having a budget of $100K with only $50K remaining, even though that first $50K should have come out of BPAF #1.\r\n\r\n'),(548,'When you finish entering a bpaf you still need to enter the legalrefno and you need to get the bpafrefno. So the system should immediately open up the same bpaf you just entered for editing so that you can do this. Saves a lot of work. ','',''),(546,'A contractor level user is allowed to look at just the things associated with their company. Only bpafs and invoices from their company and only project information that relates to projects they are working on and even then just what they are involved in (in other words, they can\'t see how much money is approved for a project, just how much money is approved for them). And so forth.','',''),(547,'It looks nice but the calculations for budget in a project are way off now.  I have one project that is showing as having about 5x the budget it really has.\r\n \r\nScott Maxwell\r\nCode Cobblers, Inc.','',''),(549,'When you enter a bpaf there is no lawyer assigned. \r\nThere are a few ways to handle this: \r\n* I think my previous proposal was to have a \"not assigned\" lawyer be one of the options.\r\n* Allow the lawyer field to be left blank. \r\n* We could also allow the field to be left blank but then detect whatever that leaves in the and replace it with \"not assigned\" \r\n\r\nThe first is easier but if someone deletes or hides the lawyer the system is unusable (well you have to enter bogus lawyers into the system). \r\n\r\n','','I think this has been fixed. Lawyers are no longer required. '),(550,'If you want the spendable to be 0 you could leave it blank -- it implies the same thing. The system could simply put a zero there saving one more field that the user needs to fill in.','',''),(551,'We want to be able to log changes so that we can tell what the status of a bpaf used to be. Mostly this is useful for the change in status on bpafs so userinterface should be concentrated there but everything should be logged so that someone with access to the raw database could back things out if they had to. \r\n\r\nThe goal for the bpaf system would be to have the ability to look at the status of a bpaf at some earlier point in time. The easiest way to do this would probably be to create a bpafhistory table that has all the fields of a bpaf plus a date/time stamp and a new seq#. Then, whenever a bpaf record changes, we simply save a copy of the old one in the history table before we make the change. At any time one could step back through the history of a particular record to see how it\'s changed over time. I recommend that we ignore changes to the project numbers since you\'re not really supposed to change that and focus on the fields inside the bpaf records such as \"status\" and \"last change\" and \"notes\" that will change. \r\n\r\nFor non-bpaf changes, I\'m thinking about a table that records inserts, updates and deletes along with the time and data and the user. That way an admin can go back and figure out what happened to data that was lost but only in an extreme case. \r\n\r\nKeep in mind that the whole database is backed up every night. ','',''),(552,'Script to insert user \'admin\' into the database is not specifying the columns of the insertion','',''),(553,'The validation in the current running invoice tracker prevents someone from entering a record with a bpaf date after the Next Step date.\r\nIt is a common practice to enter a bpaf date in the future (as in, this contract is for an event that happens at the end of the month) and, of course, the next step start would be today (pretty much always). SO \"next step start\" will often be before the effective start.','',''),(554,'The calculation for the project summary is wrong. \r\n\r\nHere is the correct calculation. \r\n\r\nFor each project look in the budget table. The start date is the latest start date before today. The end date is the start date+duration. The \"raw bucket\" (which should properly be called \"budget\") is the amount associated with that record. If there is no record whose start date - end date interval includes today then that project\'s budget is 0.  The bpaf table plays no part in this calculation. \r\n\r\nIn the project summary table the \"contract start\" and \"contract end\" should be \"budget start\" and \"budget end\" and the \"raw bucket\" should be \"budget amount\".\r\n\r\nThe amound spent on a project is the sum of all the line items in invoices between the start and end date for that project. \r\nLeft is the difference between budget and the amount spent. Burn rate is the amount spent divided by the number of months between the start of the interval and today. And Months is the number of months, at that burn rate, that it will take to use up the rest of the budget.\r\n\r\nOnce we get this right we probably want to add a selector which will pick a fiscal year (not sure how to do that) so that you can look at the project summary for last year or the year before or for next year (next year\'s project summary won\'t have amounts spent but will have the budget amount).\r\n','',''),(555,'1) I tried to sort by effective date and it is sorting correctly by month-day-year, not by year-month-day','',''),(556,'When you are viewing something it\'s natural to want to edit what you see so we should put a link from view to edit and not make people go back. ','',''),(557,'Just add up all the amounts and show it at the bottom of the page. Often this will not mean anything but it leaves it up to the user to create a view that DOES mean something. ','',''),(558,'If there are more than one project, just pick the first one you see but put a * or some other icon to indicate that there are more projects. The truth is that most invoices have only project. ','',''),(559,'If there are more than one project, just pick the first one you see but put a * or some other icon to indicate that there are more projects. The truth is that most Bpafs have only 1 project. ','',''),(560,'We need to be able to search bpafs. We want be able to search several fields, but especially the various note fields. ','',''),(561,'search on all fields','',''),(562,'The information about companies should include (in addition to company name and contact name) \r\nTax Id Number\r\nState of incorporation\r\nphone number\r\nfax number\r\naddress\r\nemail address\r\nNONE of this should be required but including it allows someone to get this information (which is necessary for writing a BPAF) from our database instead of looking around elsewhere.','',''),(563,'The purpose would be to have a form with relatively little information which then expands into all the information in a BPAf. Then you could copy and paste that information into the bpaf and click on a link and cause a record in the bpaf database to be created. \r\n\r\n\r\nThe form would contain\r\nProject - pull down of projects\r\nContractor - pull down of companies\r\nManager -- new table or just a text field\r\nRate -- fill in\r\nHours -- fill in\r\nAmount -- calculate rate*hours\r\nStatement of Work -- big text field\r\nStart Date\r\nEnd Date\r\n\r\n\r\nA bpaf contains\r\nOriginating department (always \"Tools Group\")\r\nContracting Party -- company\r\nContact name -- from company information\r\nTax ID Number -- from company information\r\nState of incorporation  -- from company information\r\nPhone number -- from company information\r\nFax Number -- from company information\r\naddress -- from company information\r\nemail -- from company information\r\n\"will the contracting party provide services to scea\" -- always \"Yes\"\r\n\"number ow w2 employees\" -- always 2\r\nREason or purpose for agreement -- kind of a complicated text generated from other information\r\nNOTE: In the following statement \"%\" represents a new line and <xxx> represents the data in the xxx field. \r\n%<project name>%%<company> will provide engineering services at an average rate of $<rate>/man hour.%%Total Monetary Value estimated based on the following projects and man-hour estimates:%<hours> man hours to implement features including:%<statement of work>%<Company> to provide provide twice monthly invoices.%Project oversight and review of deliverables to be performed by \",<manager>\r\nTotal monetary value: Amount followed by the word \"even\"\r\nStart: \r\nEnd:\r\nApprover 1 -- manager\r\nAprover 2 -- RJ (unless RJ is the manager)\r\n\r\n\r\n','',''),(564,'Currently the default page length is 25. It should be set to whatever the maximum is. ','',''),(565,'every page should have the same favicon so that a user can see at a glance that a particular tab in his browser is another page of the invoice tracker. \r\n\r\nI don\'t really care WHAT the icon is, as long as it\'s unique. Could we do a little invoice (square with lines on it)? Or maybe a pen because that\'s what the main page image is. Or a spyglass? ','',''),(566,'The work flow is made harder by the fact that I can\'t enter the legal ref number when I first enter the record -- I have to go back and edit the number in. ','',''),(567,'Not sure what the complete field means but if it\'s set the bpaf doesn\'t show up in the Pending Bpaf list. \r\n\r\nSo new bpafs which are correctly entered but are not finished (one meaning of complete) or canceled are not showing up in the pending bpaf page. ','',''),(568,'If a bpaf isn\'t assigned an attorney -- that is, it\'s left with the attorney set at the default value (no attorney) then when it does the pending bpaf join the bpaf gets left off. \r\n\r\nIt obviously isn\'t complete so it doesn\'t get put on the Complete bpaf list and it has a legalref so it\'s not on the incomplete list. \r\n\r\nSo it\'s effectively off any radar. ','','This bug was caused by allowing users to leave the attorney field blank. Since we now have an attorney \"Not Assigned\", we can make it mandatory again. \r\n\r\nThe other possibility is to do that vodoo you do so well with the select to make it show up even tho it has no attorney. \r\n\r\nBut what other attorney-related joins are we doing that are causing it to disappear? '),(569,'The table has almost half it\'s list taken up with the prefix column. ','',''),(570,'In the pending bpafs (and other pages) it has a \"hide info\" link. It would be good if it remembered this (as a cookie?) permanently (from one session to the next).','',''),(571,'in error code \"Please check the items bellow.\"  \"bellow\" is misspelled; the proper spelling is \"below\"','','This problem is in most of the file in the library that have \"ctl\" in the filename. '),(572,'add filters the invoice and bpaf lists in the section that now contains the company filter\r\nAlso Filter on attorney, start, alarm. These would be related by \"and\" but \"all\" would match any value for that field. \r\n\r\nI\'m not sure it would work but it would be nice if one could also select date and amount ranges. ','',''),(573,'Bpaf descriptions could be very long\r\nThis would show up in view and edit but not in any list','',''),(574,'At the top of various lists there is a link to the add record page for that kind of record. This should be \"add invoice\" or \"add bpaf\" or whatever','',''),(575,'In the lists the \"first\" link should be called \"First\" (upper case \"F\")','',''),(576,'I have no confidence in the company and project summaries. It\'s not that I doubt that you implemented them correctly. I am concerned that the data might be in error. Or, possibly, that the algorithm might be wrong. \r\nTo resolve this,  I would like a \"detail\" button for every summary line. \r\nThe detail page would show (for any selected company or project)  all the bpafs associated with that and all the invoices associated with every bpaf (that is, a list of bpafs as section headers with the sections consisting of the invoices against each bpaf with totals).  It would also show the information in the summary line at the top for reference. Note that it would only do this for one bpaf or project at a time.\r\nMy goal here is to be able to find problems in the data -- or algorithm, whatever it is -- or to prove that the information is correct. \r\n\r\nThese two pages are really the HEART  of the whole system and, until we get them to work properly (which in this case means in a way that is correct beyond dispute), we haven\'t actually justified our system. \r\n','',''),(577,'If the summary page calculations would indicate that we\'re about to run out of money (within then next 8 weeks) we should send an email to the responsible manager on the project. ','','It may be that each project needs a manager and that each manager needs to be put in a database. Actually I already added a manager table because of another project I\'m working on.'),(578,'I was putting in an invoice into the T&T tracker and the drop down menu for the available BPAFs included a canceled BPAF (CAR0017). Eeek!','',''),(579,'EEEk and BPAFs that are not yet completed! (CAR0016)','',''),(580,'The invoices to be considered in the calculation and, therefore, in the detail pages are all invoices associated with currently approved bpafs for the company in question without considering dates (date sent x bpaf effstart) and projects.\r\n\"So the proper algorithmic thing to do is to ignore dates, ignore projects and only pay attention to which invoices are associated with that bpaf. \r\nYou can\'t not put it on the list because, by your algorithm, it won\'t be on ANY list and that\'s MUCH worse than having it on the wrong list.\"','',''),(581,'According to an email chain, bpafs that have been cancelled are still available in the pulldown to be assigned to invoices. \r\n\r\nCase in point ACC0014\r\n\r\nI have not checked any of this information; for all I know it\'s possible that ACC0014 was assigned to the invoices AND THEN canceled (that would be really hard to fix) but I\'m TOLD that it was in the pull down AFTER it was canceled. ','','Access Softek  69775    ACC0014     04/28/2008  05/02/2008  2997.00  View  Edit  Delete \r\nAccess Softek  69788    ACC0014     05/05/2008  05/05/2008  5697.00  View  Edit  Delete \r\nAccess Softek  69799    ACC0014     05/12/2008  05/12/2008  7992.00  View  Edit  Delete \r\n'),(582,'See \"Additional information\" for background on the \"hidden\" status for values.\r\n\r\nIn the bpaf edit page the company is pulldown which means that if the company is hidden it doesn\'t show up in the pulldown. The effect of this is that the pulldowns has \"select\" selected and you can\'t save the bpaf and you can\'t select the correct company because it\'s hidden. \r\n\r\nI have no clue how to fix this but it will be true of any value that can be hidden and is shown as a pulldown in the edit page. \r\nMaybe the rule should be that you can edit a page to be a hidden value but you can\'t set something to a hidden value when you are ADDING a new record. This is imperfect but compromises. \r\n\r\nTo repro, select a company that has a bpaf associated with it. Set that company\'s status to \"hidden\" and then try to edit a bpaf for that company. Try to save it -- I dare you! :)\r\n\r\nThere same problem will exist (probably) with projects, attorneys and anything else that has a possible \"hidden\" status. \r\n','','\"Hidden\" companies (hidden anything) is supposed to be able to be displayed anywhere it\'s needed but simply not changed to. The idea is that you hide a company, project, etc, so that the pulldowns don\'t get cluttered up with obsolete crap and infinitely long.  '),(583,'When you add an invoice, the \"bpaf ref\" pulldown says \"Loading bpafs\", seemingly forever. And the \"List bpafs\" link doesn\'t seem to do anything. \r\n\r\nFor example, company \"test\" has 2 bpafs TES0000 and TES0001. Each has a valid spendable amount ($10k) and each has projects associated with it and each has a status of complete. Both have an effective start date in the past and an effective end date in the future. 2 bpafs, perfectly valid and complete, as far as I can tell. \r\n\r\nAdd an invoice and select \"test\" as the company. \r\n\r\nNotice that the \"BPAF Ref\" pulldown never changes. \r\n\r\nClick on the \"list Bpafs\" (by the way, BPAF is an acronym and, as such, all letters should be capitalized) and notice that nothing happens. \r\n','',''),(584,'Apostrophes are appearing with their escape commands twice it seems. If I enter into a field: \"Kellen\'s ^uber^ test project\", it becomes \"Kellen\\\'s ^uber^ test project\".\r\n\r\nIt seems to affect most if not all text fields.','',''),(585,'In the change password page of the admin tab it allows the user (or anyone else) to change the password of any logged in account without entering the current password. If, say, I forgot to lock my computer at night and someone walked up to my browser, they could lock me out of my account or steal it with very little effort.','',''),(586,'If possible, I think it would be really useful to be able to click on a column to sort it by both first to last (as exists now), and also last to first (very useful for dates at least). ','',''),(587,'Get an existing invoice (or create one). In the Project Allocations Section, click on \"edit\". When the project comes up to edit, select a different project and click \"update\". \r\n\r\nThe new project is added to the list. \r\n\r\nI would expect that the old project would be changed (that is, same amount of money, different project name). \r\n\r\nIf you change the money instead of the project name, it works as I would expect. ','','I base my belief that this is a bug on the following simple rule: add should add records, edit/update should only change existing records. This looks like an edit that does an add. '),(588,'Include date (which should be used to determine \"currently\" approved BPAFs and contemporaneous invoices) in the Summary Pages (Company and Project Summary Pages)','',''),(589,'There is no option to write in a legalrefno for an invoice; it should not show up as a column in the invoice list page.','',''),(590,'somewhere around 144 in the middle of the array that collects the data\r\n','',''),(591,'in both the rows with names and the columns with names, blank names may contain data that needs to be ignored; in any event they need to be reported\r\n','',''),(592,'Currently lists of names on the rows are being checked but the columns are not being checked. \r\n\r\nThis is hard because the we don\'t have the array until we\'ve built it and by then it\'s overwritten the old one. Or has it? \r\n\r\nAnyway, build it in a temporary place and, blah blah blah\r\n','',''),(593,'right now when it reads a line that contains names it performs a series of checks right then and there\r\n\r\nit should call a function, mainly because that way I can do the same thing with columns of names\r\n','',''),(594,'function attribtype($attrib){\r\n\r\nverify it\'s no longer called and remove it','',''),(595,'function findattributecolumn($drinknames, $attributetag=\"Attributes\"){\r\n','',''),(596,'function starts_with_string($needle, $haystack){\r\n','',''),(597,'function convertattribute($attribute){\r\n','',''),(598,'function convert_attrib_to_value($attribute){\r\n','',''),(599,'function loaddatabase($fname, $attributetag=\"Attributes\" ){// get the data out of the data file\r\n','',''),(600,'When reading the names from the first column (as distinct from the first row) it append the names to the list. If it\'s already read from the first row then all the names are duplicated.','',''),(601,'Drink attributes is sparse but not empty\r\nExistential blue should have the attribute \"flaming\" and it doesn\'t. ','',''),(602,'drink ingredients has drinks with sizes but no ingredients','',''),(603,'for consistency and correctness','',''),(604,'for consistency and correctness','',''),(605,'for consistency and correctness','',''),(606,'check to see if a drink has the right attribute ','',''),(607,'check for correctness\r\n','',''),(608,'check for correctness','','');
