INSERT INTO `mantis_bugnote_text_table` VALUES (1,'I think it\'s in one of these selects, probably in the field list. \r\n\r\nMYSQL.PHP\r\nX 934:getArchives       $result = mysql_query( \"SELECT $psttbl.id,date FROM $psttbl ,$cattbl  WHERE ext1!=\'hide\' and $psttbl.cat=$cattbl.id and $cattbl.private!=1 and $psttbl.private!=1 ORDER by date DESC\" )\r\nX 930:getArchives       $sql=\"select $psttbl.id,$psttbl.title,$psttbl.private,$cattbl.id,$cattbl.cat,$cattbl.private,$authtbl.id,$authtbl.auth_name,$readtbl.auth,$readtbl.cat from $psttbl,$cattbl,$authtbl,$readtbl where ($psttbl.private=0 and $cattbl.private=0 and $cattbl.id=$psttbl.cat and $readtbl.auth=$authid and $authtbl.id=$authid and $readtbl.cat=$psttbl.cat)\r\nX 692:getCats       $sql=\"SELECT $tbl.id,$tbl.cat,$tbl.private FROM $tbl,$readtbl where ($readtbl.cat=$tbl.id and $readtbl.auth=\'$authid\' and $tbl.private=\'1\')\r\nX 687:      $result = mysql_query( \"SELECT id,cat,private FROM $tbl where private!=1 ORDER by id DESC \")\r\nX 411:getPosts      $result = mysql_query( \"SELECT $psttbl.id,title FROM $psttbl ,$cattbl  where $psttbl.cat=$cattbl.id and $cattbl.private!=1 and $psttbl.private!=1 ORDER by date DESC\" )\r\nX 407:getPosts       $sql=\"select $psttbl.id,$psttbl.title from $psttbl,$cattbl,$authtbl,$readtbl where (($psttbl.private=0 and $cattbl.private=0 and $cattbl.id=$psttbl.cat and $readtbl.auth=$authid and $authtbl.id=$authid and $readtbl.cat=$psttbl.cat)\r\nX 411:getPosts      $result = mysql_query( \"SELECT $psttbl.id,title FROM $psttbl ,$cattbl  where $psttbl.cat=$cattbl.id and $cattbl.private!=1 and $psttbl.private!=1 ORDER by date DESC\" )\r\nX 407:getPosts        $sql=\"select $psttbl.id,$psttbl.title from $psttbl,$cattbl,$authtbl,$readtbl where (($psttbl.private=0 and $cattbl.private=0 and $cattbl.id=$psttbl.cat and $readtbl.auth=$authid and $authtbl.id=$authid and $readtbl.cat=$psttbl.cat)\r\nX 266:getSPost      $result = mysql_query( \"SELECT $list FROM $psttbl,$cattbl WHERE $psttbl.id=\'$id\' AND $psttbl.ext1!=\'$adm\' and $psttbl.cat=$cattbl.id and $cattbl.private!=1 and $psttbl.private!=1 \" )\r\nX 261:getSPost        $sql=\"select $psttbl.id,$psttbl.title,$psttbl.private,$cattbl.id,$cattbl.cat,$cattbl.private,$authtbl.id,$authtbl.auth_name,$readtbl.auth,$readtbl.cat from $psttbl,$cattbl,$authtbl,$readtbl where ($psttbl.private=0 and $cattbl.private=0 and $cattbl.id=$psttbl.cat and $readtbl.auth=$authid and $authtbl.id=$authid and $readtbl.cat=$psttbl.cat)\r\nX 226:getDateList       $result = mysql_query( \"SELECT date FROM $psttbl ,$cattbl where $psttbl.cat=$cattbl.id and $cattbl.private!=1 and $psttbl.private!=1 ORDER by date DESC\" )\r\nX 220:getDataList        $sql=\"select $psttbl.id,$psttbl.title,$psttbl.private,$cattbl.id,$cattbl.cat,$cattbl.private,$authtbl.id,$authtbl.auth_name,$readtbl.auth,$readtbl.cat from $psttbl,$cattbl,$authtbl,$readtbl where ($psttbl.private=0 and $cattbl.private=0 and $cattbl.id=$psttbl.cat and $readtbl.auth=$authid and $authtbl.id=$authid and $readtbl.cat=$psttbl.cat)\r\nX 168:getFieldList  $result = mysql_query($sql)\r\nX 74:getPostList    $result= mysql_query($sql)\r\n\r\n\r\nSEARCH MYSQL\r\nX 47:       $result=mysql_query(\"SELECT $tbl.id,title,author,$tbl.date $data_flag FROM $tbl , $cat_tbl where $cat_tbl.id=$tbl.cat and $tbl.ext1!=\'hide\' and $cat_tbl.private!=1 and $tbl.private!=1\")'),(2,'I went through all the selects on the list. Two or three of them DID have different field lists and I\'m pretty sure that WOULD make a difference. But both this bug and bug #2 are still active. \r\n\r\nI\'m going to check out the old version of this software and see if I can isolate the change (probably mysql.php but you never know).'),(3,'Score: reverting mysql.php to version 1.13 (from 1.14) which was checked in in September, removes all the bad behavior.\r\n\r\nProblem is, we changed a hell of a lot of stuff in mysql. Maybe if I change stuff back, one line at a time, we can find the culprit(s). \r\n\r\nI\'ve already stared at it a lot and I don\'t see anything wrong with the changes I know I made...'),(4,'I\'ve isolated the problem to getSpost. I did this by copying version 1.15 of mysql to mysql.php and then replacing the getSpost code from version 1.13 into it. This works, proving that the only problem with 1.15 is getSpost'),(5,'Definitely can reproduce the problem. Definitely exhibited in mysql.php r1.14, definitely not in mysql.php r1.13.\r\n\r\nLogin as dave/pass\r\nclick on any archived post\r\nclick on general category\r\nif you see any \"first post x\" articles, the problem is there\r\nif you see the post you clicked on or different posts in general, the problem is NOT there. '),(6,'I\'ve isolated the problem down to the select in getSpost that is used when PrivateAuthorized() returns true. It\'s not the field list. \r\n\r\nThe problem was that the select didn\'t limit the articles to just those that matched $id but got everything. Don\'t know why I ended up with exactly THAT result, but that fixed it. \r\n\r\nBug #2 should be fixed, as well.\r\n\r\nChange was entirely in mysql.php and is reflected in r1.16'),(7,'set bug 1 for notes on tracking this down and fixing it.'),(8,'it was code in the admin.php page that had the tables defined as $myprefix.\"cat\" instead of $my_prefix.\"cat\" -- one wonders how this EVER worked! \r\n\r\nProbably had readwrite.php included in there and it uses hard coded prefixes...\r\n\r\nFixed now in admin.php r1.10'),(9,'He can\'t see them even if he has the read privs for all of them.'),(10,'This is almost certainly related to 10 and 11'),(11,'tested on build 10/10/04'),(12,'fixed in en.php version 1.1'),(13,'fixed in mysql 1.20 10/11/04'),(14,'fixed in mysql.php 1.20 on 10/11/04'),(15,'admin is special everywhere now :)\r\nmysql 1.20, build 10/11/04'),(16,'I think this is now resolved with mysql.php 1.20 10/11/04\r\nEssentially the admin can see everything regardless of what other cookies are there. User cookies are ignored as long as the admin cookie is there but the admin cookie goes away with the session.'),(17,'select * from bmc_write where auth=6;\r\nif (PrivateAuthorized()){\r\n$wrttbl=$my_prefix.\"write\";\r\n$authid=WhoAmI();\r\n$result = mysql_query( \"select * from bmc_write where auth=6\" ) or errd(\"MySQL Error!\",mysql_error());\r\n$num_rows = mysql_num_rows($result);\r\nif($num_rows > 0) {\r\n add link to post page\r\n}//if ($num..\r\n}//if Private\r\nAll this needs to happen where we have the login link'),(18,'select * from bmc_write,bmc_cats where bmc_write.auth=6 and bmc_write.cat=bmc_cats.id;'),(19,'select * from bmc_write,bmc_cats where bmc_write.auth=6 and bmc_write.cat=bmc_cats.id;'),(20,'select format from bmc_posts where id=5;'),(21,'select format from bmc_posts where id=5;'),(22,'one link is index.php?id=# where # is a post number\r\nthat\'s the only one I could find'),(23,'This is actually done in doDat() with the parameter being the post number'),(24,'inc/mysql/admin.mysql.php:553:function doDat(...) {\r\ninc/mysql/main.mysql.php:129:function doDat($in=null,$arr=null) {\r\ninc/mysql/priv.mysql.php:552:function doDat(...) {'),(25,'The actual message is displayed by: \r\ninclude CFG_ROOT.\"/inc/templates/\".CFG_THEME.\"/main.template.php\";\r\nSo this will need to be reworked.'),(26,'there was some odd code in privpost and writetest that prevented it from working. mostly typos'),(27,'There are 3 parts to this task. First we need to add a link to the page that allows us to edit the description. This is in case: display_gallery. This should have a flag to indicate  that we\'re editng a descrption and which item is being edited. \r\n\r\nSecond, we need to catch this flag. I\'m thinking we should do this where we test for the admin mode and change the config_array page type to be \"page edit\" but that might not be the best way. If we do that then we can have another page that is the edit description page. It should show the picture, the old description and have a form that allows us to enter a new description.\r\n\r\nThird we need to actually change the description. Still working on that one.'),(28,'The description is stored in the product array so all we have to do is to change that and the description changes. \r\n\r\nAlso, to create the page for images, we need to change the template. Use the template for the display gallery page but remove the loop...'),(29,'The URL flag for edit descriptions is mode=editdesc, the template is edit_desc.tpl and the page type is \"edit_description\"'),(30,'I got the links in by changing line to \r\n<pre>\r\n	$description_array[$key] = $product_array[$value]. \'<br><br><center><b>| Replace Image | <a href=\"\'.$url.\'index.php?currentlist=\'.$current_list.\'&mode=editdesc&item=\'.$key.\'\"> Edit Description </a>|</b></center>\';\r\n</pre>\r\nitem value is in $description_array. How to get that into the template is a good question. Also it never gets to the right template because it get\'s changed after I set it. But the link is right.\n\nedited on: 11-09-04 16:11'),(31,'new version created on puddingproof ending 11/13'),(32,'version saved on puddingproof 11/13/04'),(33,'all the sub items have been completed as of 11/13/04\r\nthe code is on puddingproof/storebot2'),(34,'Actually, linkage text already shows up under the picture so we could do that whereever we deem it necessary, as long as we don\'t want to use linkage text.'),(35,'we now have admin functions'),(36,'We finished the pieces so the meta bug can be closed.'),(37,'This is because I have a version that doesn\'t have GD.'),(38,'This link should be added to \r\n457 $description_array[$key] = $\r\n\r\nIt should be something like \"&mode=logout\" and then you catch this, delete the cookie and reset the header.'),(39,'no, I\'ve decided that, with cookies, this isn\'t necessary.'),(40,'All the sub items are done.'),(41,'I think this means that you can upload something to the file. If the name is the same as an existing file, it replaces that file. If it\'s different, it creates a new file. There is not need for differentiation.'),(42,'for starters I\'ve added a new page case called \"uploadpix\"  as expressed in config_array[\'page_type\']. \r\n$upload_pix_flag is the flag for it\r\nsubmode=uploadpix\r\nthe template name is uploadpix.tpl\r\nI don\'t know what it does or how but I know how I call it and where it is!'),(43,'after you upload it you have to save it to the right place.\r\ndon\'t need a page\r\nsave_pix_flag\r\nsubmode=save_pix'),(44,'This fixes the displaying of the images. However now some of them are large and some are small. This is because the image size array is not out of alignment with the catalog array. Should be an easy fix for this...\r\n\r\nYeah! Sort the image_array, not the catalog array and all is well.'),(45,'These fixes have been added.'),(46,'taken care of in most recent version'),(47,'finished'),(48,'fixed in most recent version'),(49,'fixed in most recent version'),(50,'All the elements should be fixed now.'),(51,'fixed in 1.11'),(52,'fixed in 1.11'),(53,'fixed in 1.11 \r\nmay need to be moved around but it\'s htere!'),(54,'fixed in 1.11 (Actually says \"expenses\" and is hilited slightely differently)'),(55,'We\'re going to allow values in the pulldown from max(foryear) to min(foryear)+1. We\'re going to assume explicitely that all numbers bettwen min(foryear)+1 and max(foryear) are in the database. If they aren\'t it makes a mess (lots of errors) but I don\'t see a remedy. \r\n\r\nWhat we really want is for it to show $year-1 (i.e. \"$lastyear\") only if such a thing exists in the database. But it makes my head hurt to think about the amount of work THAT would be...'),(56,'create table pledges (name varchar(30), date date, pledge decimal (9,2), tstamp timestamp);'),(57,'created table pledges in database budget (maybe that\'s the wrong place but it will do for now)'),(58,'create table contribution (Name varchar(30),Year int,Jan decimal (9,2),Feb decimal (9,2),Mar decimal (9,2),Apr decimal (9,2),May decimal (9,2),Jun decimal (9,2),Jul decimal (9,2),Aug decimal (9,2),Sep decimal (9,2),Oct decimal (9,2),Nov decimal (9,2), December decimal (9,2),Stamp timestamp);'),(59,'added contribution table to budget database'),(60,'fixed in version 1.12'),(61,'fixed in version 1.15 of budgetreport.php and version 1.4 of budgetfuncs.php\n\nedited on: 01-04-05 13:07'),(62,'fixed in version 1.15 of budgetreport.php and version 1.4 of budgetfuncs.php'),(63,'Fixed in version 1.16 of budgetreport.php and version 1.5 of budgetfuncs.php'),(64,'This is supposed to go on the budgetreport page.'),(65,'fixed in budgetreport.php 1.18\n\nedited on: 01-05-05 12:17'),(66,'added this feature in version 1.4 of install.php'),(67,'fixed it 2/16; should be in tenant.php 1.4 and tenantsummary.tpl 1.4'),(68,'In summary & detail item displays , there is a ACTIVE/HIDDEN selector and a delete checkbox.\r\nThe only issue is (I think) that the delete flag is ignored. The reason is that we don\'t have much data and I\'m not ready to actually delete any of it until I have more! :)\n\nedited on: 03-31-05 09:13'),(69,'Summary has code in it that shows whether the delete flag is checked in the sense that it shows it checked. This needs to be removed by and by. \r\n\r\nDetail has no such code; bugs entered on this can be ignored since neither one is supposed to have such code!'),(70,'fixed problem in tenantsummary.tpl r1.3'),(71,'Well, it\'s consistent; it happens EVERY time.'),(72,'it was set up so that every time I set the space number it called the item summary routine'),(73,'Should be fixed in tenant.php 1.5'),(74,'that\'s because they have spaceno set to 0. \r\nThen you edit them on the detail page and it get\'s set to 1\r\nWE got a problem in both places'),(75,'It seems to work now but I don\'t know what I changed so I\'m somewhat suspicious'),(76,'Nope. Problem seems to be that we see a cookie but it doesn\'t have any information in it. Also, I\'m looking at the cookie and it has a 10 in it! That\'s not right.'),(77,'And the cookie goes away! How can THAT happen?!'),(78,'Removed all the cookie code (for spaces, I mean) and problem went away. The problem seems to be that I can\'t set the space into a cookie and then retrieve it again, reliably. I pass the ISSET(_COOKIE[foo]) test but then can\'t get information out of _COOKIE[foo] for some reason. a real pisser'),(79,'I know why. The login page specifies where to return you. It was returning you to login.php and now it\'s sending you to tenant.php. Neither is correct. \r\n\r\nOne possibility is to have two login pages and to pass the appropriate page to the WMGetAuthenticated routein. \r\n\r\nAnother (better?) one is to simply pass the url of the page to call when returning. So I call it and pass tenant.php, login.php or admin.php and we wind up at the top of that page when we\'re done.'),(80,'Added code to have loginutil pass the PHP_SELF value to the template which then uses that as the action for the form. Seems to handle it.'),(81,'This belongs in the celemp section.'),(82,'Yep, I now sort the array and it seems to complete solve this problem, as well as putting the images in some non-arbitrary order.'),(83,'moved the logout button to the top of the page, where it belongs'),(84,'I believe this has been fixed.'),(85,'This is apparently a problem with my PHP installation on TheBrain. Lord knows I\'ve gone through enough trouble trying to fix it.'),(86,'Storebot development and deployment will be (must be) done on systems that have GD working.'),(87,'This has been added at or before 1.31'),(88,'This has been added by 1.31'),(89,'I believe this has all been fixed by version 1.31'),(90,'Problem was itemno and spaceno not being called the same thing in all cases'),(91,'the problem was that itemno and spaceno wasn\'t always the same.'),(92,'Apparently, it has something to do with the url Wally is using. \r\nhttp://www.panogreetings.com/index.php?admin_pass=password&itemname=Array&current_list=&list_item=&mode=admin\r\nIN theory this should work but in practice it doesn\'t REALLY log you in.'),(93,'Just added the valign=top to the culprit <td> and we\'re good.'),(94,'I was doing a string comparison instead of a numeric comparison. Also, I added something to sort the Menconi\'s last no matter what their actual score.'),(95,'I think Wally was using a URL that contained the password of the admin. Although the browser would bring up a cached page, the system wouldn\'t actually go into admin mode (I think because the code that sets the cookie wasn\'t actually called). \r\n\r\nIf this HAD worked we would have had a horrible security hole; as it was it didn\'t work but Wally thought it should. \r\n\r\nI\'m going to lower the priority but leave the bug open so it can be reviewed.'),(96,'Struggled with this a bit (because some games have more than one winner and what to do then?) but ultimately decided to list all games with a winner and include who that winner was along with the gameeventid (which will save me oodles of time when there is a problem).'),(97,'I fixed this on 3/17/05 version 1.18 in both blfuncs and dataentry'),(98,'I\'m not going to retest this.'),(99,'I\'m not going to retest this.'),(100,'I\'m not going to retest this.'),(101,'There is also a problem that the url for the blank.gif image is supposedly http://67.113.154.163/pix/blank.gif which is wrong since it should be http://67.113.154.163/what/pix/blank.gif'),(102,'171 is the bug in the login system that this is related to'),(103,'And the verify password field is in the clear!'),(104,'The page designers will determine this.\n\nedited on: 03-31-05 08:46'),(107,'This is somewhat different now but the key question remains the same: does the delete check mark work or now? '),(105,'certainly fixed by tenantsummary.tpl 1.8 3/26/05'),(106,'There are two components of this. First, we need to make the $message variable available to all templates. Also, we need to make sure that all routines that call templates must have a $message variable. \r\n\r\nThen we must make sure that the proto-templates (at least) display the message somewhere. \r\n\r\nWe should also evaluate the need for $message now that we have smartyvalidate.'),(108,'certainly fixed by tenantsummary.tpl 1.8 3/26/05'),(109,'the login routines have been fixed certainly by loginutil.php 1.9 3/30/05'),(110,'fixed in install.php 1.10 3/10/05\r\nShould, of course, be tested.'),(111,'Still broken as of mysql.php 1.9'),(112,'Added Get_SmartyTemplate to miscfunc.php as of 1.9 3/31/05 (actually considerably before this point) but not entirely satisfied with results. It turns out that different routines want different things passed along.'),(113,'We never call those routines. I can\'t figure out how I would use it -- I\'d have to have many lines of info at the bottom of the page...'),(114,'We\'d like to have a record of every transaction that happens on Whatchamall. At the moment, I don\'t know how to do this and I\'m not sure IF we can do it at all. Here\'s why:\r\n\r\nThe user buys something by clicking on \"add to cart\" and going to paypal. That \"add to cart\" button goes straight to paypal (it does not pass go or collect $200) and paypal considers that transaction to be between the tenant and his customer. Paypal will not return any information to US. \r\n\r\nIt might be possible to have some kind of a rube-goldberg mechanism such that clicking on the \"add to cart\" actually calls OUR web site which logs the transaction and then forwards to paypal. \r\n\r\nHmm. Why not.'),(115,'http://67.113.154.163/what/tenant.php?mode=itemsummary&spaceno=1 has both an add an item form and a add a cateogory form'),(116,'We\'ve change the phrase database so that every phrase has a name instead of a number. That name is, presumably, in english (although I suppose it could be in any language or actually be a number, for that matter). But it\'s unique and when you add a phrase in some other language it will have the same name. \r\n\r\nThus this problem may be handled but it\'s all so new I wouldn\'t bet on it.'),(117,'as noted in the bug'),(118,'There are better routines available in this language than print_r and print. If we go with something that tells us more information about the variable the debugging might get a lot better (although if it has too much information that would be bad). \r\n\r\nAlso it would be good to print the information into a buffer and then put it on the screen or into the log file as necessary, instead of having the two destinations as separate code paths.'),(119,'debug.php 1.7 or earlier 4/1/05'),(120,'from http://www.php.net/manual/en/ref.var.php\r\nvar_dump -- Dumps information about a variable\r\nvar_export -- Outputs or returns a parsable string representation of a variable\r\nempty -- Determine whether a variable is empty\r\ndebug_zval_dump -- Dumps a string representation of an internal zend value to output\r\ngettype -- Get the type of a variable\r\nis_array -- Finds whether a variable is an array\r\nisset -- Determine whether a variable is set\r\n\r\nVery useful to analyze an array while debugging.\r\nfunction parray($array,$prep = \'\') {\r\n/* (c) by Roland Tapken <tapken@engter.de> */\r\n$prep = \"$prep|\";\r\nwhile(list($key,$val) = each($array)) {\r\n$type = gettype($val);\r\nif(is_array($val)) {\r\n$line = \"-+ $key ($type)\\n\";\r\n$line .= parray($val,\"$prep \");\r\n} else {\r\n$line = \"-&gt; $key = \\\"$val\\\" ($type)\\n\";\r\n}\r\n$ret .= $prep.$line;\r\n}\r\nreturn $ret;\r\n}\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n$array = array(\"test\",2,array(\"foo\" => \"bar\"), 4.23);\r\necho \"<pre>\";\r\necho parray($array);\r\necho \"</pre>\";\r\nThis will print:\r\n|-> 0 = \"test\" (string)\r\n|-> 1 = \"2\" (integer)\r\n|-+ 2 (array)\r\n| |-> foo = \"bar\" (string)\r\n|-> 3 = \"4.23\" (double)'),(121,'I fixed this a while back'),(122,'I added a name field to the phrase database so that every phrase has a unique name. This can be used as the unary index shared across