pany C has BPAFs for will show up in the pull down menu in the Project Allocations section.\r\n\r\n-          view BPAFs from company C\r\n\r\n-          Change user Aâ€™s password\r\n\r\n-          View systemâ€™s version'),(515,'This problem was associated with projects that has an apostrophe in the name.\r\nSCEA_ITS_2.3'),(516,'Log is in the `it` folder (audit.log) â€¦ can be configured in the config.php'),(517,'SCEA_ITS_2.3 (legalrefno was removed from the search fields)'),(518,'SCEA_ITS_2.3'),(519,'It was agreed that this feature would not be included in the release SCEA_ITS_2.3.'),(520,'A notification is sent every time an invoice is added or â€˜editedâ€™. So if an old invoice is edited and the company or project doesnâ€™t have any â€œcurrentlyâ€ approved BPAF with enough money, then a notification will be sent to project managers. Notification will work as follows:\r\n\r\nWhen a project is running/ran out of money, the project manager will be notified.\r\n\r\nWhen a company is running/ran out of money, then a notification will be sent to all project managers of projects that company has BPAFs for. So if company A has BPAF for project 1, project 2 and project 3. All project managers from these projects should receive the notification.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nInitially all projects will have â€˜Manager Temporaryâ€™ as its manager (this allows the current database be ported to the new database schema).'),(521,'Now the summary pages have a Date input field that should determine what is â€œcurrentlyâ€ approved bpafs and â€œcontemporaneousâ€ invoices. If this field is left in blank, then â€œdateâ€ is not considered in the calculations, so everything will be â€œCurrentâ€.\r\n\r\nDefault value is current date.'),(522,'Confirmed fixed in 2.3'),(523,'Confirmed fixed in 2.3'),(524,'This is fixed in 2.3. However, I am confused by the need for a legalref field in the invoices page.'),(525,'Confirmed fixed, 2.3'),(526,'Confirmed fixed in 2.3'),(527,'The functionality is added, but