e nuvi spends a lot of time telling me where NOT to turn -- \"Keep left on Highway 101\" -- in places that it\'s pretty obvious not to go that way. I seldom accidentally take off ramps. \r\n4) The yellow pages data is very bad. Places that have been there for years don\'t show up. Places that have been gone for years are still on it. An update would be nice.\r\n5) The 4 Gig stick with lots of data causes the nuvi to stall for about a minute before drawing the screen.\r\n6) Using the nuvi as a mp3 player with a 4 gig stick can cause it to lock up when you load a playlist. It seems to only happen with the first playlist on the list and it doesn\'t seem to matter what IN the playlist (rename the playlist so it\'s second in the list and it works).\r\n7) Sometimes the nuvi won\'t allow me to zoom in. It seems to believe that it knows better than me what zoom level is best. Even I, a naive user, know better than a chunk of electrified silicon what my needs are!\r\n8) Shuffle works ok until it happens to hit the same song again, then it seems to keep hitting the same sequence of songs as the first time (tell me I\'m crazy). With 600 songs this is statistically unlikely.\r\n9) \r\n',0,9,0,1,'2008-04-29',NULL,'Deleted','','2011-09-08 14:26:00'),(831,8,1,'write letter to seagate','William D. Watkins - Chief Executive Officer\r\nBrian Dexheimer - President, Consumer Solutions Division\r\nTodd Abbottâ€”Executive Vice President of Sales, Marketing and Customer Service\r\nBob Whitmore - Executive Vice President and Chief Technical Officer\r\nMike Wingert - Executive Vice President and General Manager for Seagate\'s Personal Compute Products\r\nPat Kingâ€”Senior Vice President and GM, Consumer Electronics\r\n- Executive Summary\r\n-- Who I am\r\n-- why I\'m writing\r\n-- what the problem is\r\n-- summary of grievances\r\n-- what I\'m going to do next\r\n-  \r\n',1,9,0,0,'2008-04-29','2008-05-29','Done','','2009-05-15 18:54:53'),(832,10,1,'contact thor','Is he going? Does he have m