7-14','Done','','2009-05-15 18:54:53'),(893,0,1,'Structure Analysis','If you have a structure like http://www.menconi.com/bman/shelter.html (top is covered in tarp, sides are covered in shade cloth) sitting by itself, it\'s held together primarily by gravity and the tension of the tarp across the top.\r\n\r\nIf a wind comes up against it\'s side it will likely apply force to the top and either tip it over or cause it to crab walk (probably tip it). To avoid that, I plan to put rebar by each leg and attach the leg with ample duct tape. \r\n\r\nNow the force of the wind can\'t tip it over because the windward legs can\'t come up but it can force it into a trapezoidal shape. To prevent that, we need some guy lines on the windward side. They can\'t be too tight because the force would appose the tension of the tarp which is holding the whole thing togehter but they can\'t be too loose or they\'ll set up a vibration. \r\n\r\nIf the wind comes down the end or otherwise manages to get up under the roof it can apply an upward force. The roof is held on by gravity and the friction of screws. To fix that I either need to positively attach the roof (with pins or with zip ties) or to tie it down to the playa with guy lines. \r\n\r\nI can\'t think of any other forces that might act on it.\r\n\r\nI have no idea the force the \"normal\" winds can put on this kind of structure but then I only have a nominal idea of how strong rebar and cording is, not to mention 1\" emt and the tarp. I\'m planning on securing every leg (15 legs) with 24\" of 1/2\" rebar, 18\" in the ground and 6\" secured to each leg. I\'m planning on putting 6 guy lines (3 on each side, every other outside leg) each secured with a 18\" staple. The guy lines will be at an angle of 20-30 degrees and the staples will be put in at right angles to the lines. I plan to use simple knots to secure the lines (like tying a bow on a package) -- their hard to get the lines taught but however taught you get them, they stay that way. \r\n\r\nAnything I\'m missing? ',1,26,0,0,'2008-07-09','2008-07-10','Done','','2009-05-15 18:54:53'),(894,0,1,'Structure Analysis','If you have a structure like http://www.menconi.com/bman/shelter.html (top is covered in tarp, sides are covered in shade cloth) sitting by itself, it\'s held together primarily by gravity and the tension of the tarp across the top.\r\n\r\nIf a wind comes up against it\'s side it will likely apply force to the top and either tip it over or cause it to crab walk (probably tip it). To avoid that, I plan to put rebar by each leg and attach the leg with ample duct tape. \r\n\r\nNow the force of the wind can\'t tip it over because the windward legs can\'t come up but it can force it into a trapezoidal shape. To prevent that, we need some guy lines on the windward side. They can\'t be too tight because the force would appose the tension of the tarp which is holding the whole thing togehter but they can\'t be too loose or they\'ll set up a vibration. \r\n\r\nIf the wind comes down the end or otherwise manages to get up under the roof it can apply an upward force. The roof is held on by gravity and the friction of screws. To fix that I either need to positively attach the roof (with pins or with zip ties) or to tie it down to the playa with guy lines. \r\n\r\nI can\'t think of any other forces that might act on it.\r\n\r\nI have no idea the force the \"normal\" winds can put on this kind of structure but then I only have a nominal idea of how strong rebar and cording is, not to mention 1\" emt and the tarp. I\'m planning on securing every leg (15 legs) with 24\" of 1/2\" rebar, 18\" in the ground and 6\" secured to each leg. I\'m planning on putting 6 guy lines (3 on each side, every other outside leg) each secured with a 18\" staple. The guy lines will be at an angle of 20-30 degrees and the staples will be put in at right angles to the lines. I plan to use simple knots to secure the lines (like tying a bow on a package) -- their hard to get the lines taught but however taught you get them, they stay that way. \r\n\r\nAnything I\'m missing? ',1,26,0,0,'2008-07-10','2008-07-10','Done','','2009-05-15 18:54:53'),(895,700,1,'even in order by seq, status should come first','',0,6,0,0,'2008-07-10',NULL,'Active','','2013-01-12 18:13:07'),(897,41,1,'create a methodology for restful','I know how to do retful now, I just need to apply it to some specific project\r\n1) .htaccess file\r\n2) Parse the command line in the php\r\n3) Use that information, instead of the url data to determine where you go',0,5,0,1,'2008-07-10',NULL,'Deleted','','2011-09-08 14:26:00'),(898,41,1,'find more about cookies and sessions','',0,5,0,1,'2008-07-10',NULL,'Deleted','','2011-09-08 14:26:00'),(1626,4,1,'infusions: rongo\'s black','',1,26,0,0,'2010-07-27','2010-08-07','Done',NULL,'2010-08-07 16:17:14'),(1627,5,1,'infusions: tea','',1,26,0,0,'2010-07-27','2010-08-07','Done',NULL,'2010-08-07 16:17:14'),(901,10,1,'fix inability to change project in detail list','',1,6,0,0,'2008-07-14','2008-07-14','Done','','2009-05-15 18:54:53'),(1625,6,1,'infusions: bottle what I got','',1,26,0,0,'2010-07-27','2010-08-01','Done',NULL,'2010-08-01 19:05:07'),(903,700,1,'in detail list the status isn\'t correctly displayed','',0,6,0,0,'2008-07-14',NULL,'Active','','2013-01-12 18:13:07'),(904,9,1,'make a list of items to purchase','',1,26,0,0,'2008-07-17','2008-07-28','Done','','2009-05-15 18:54:53'),(905,10,1,'gromet the shade cloth I have','',1,26,0,0,'2008-07-17','2008-07-27','Done','','2009-05-15 18:54:53'),(906,10,1,'buy 8\" bungies','',1,26,0,0,'2008-07-17','2008-07-27','Done','','2009-05-15 18:54:53'),(907,10,1,'get 20x20 tarp (cheap!)','',1,26,0,0,'2008-07-17','2008-07-27','Done','','2009-05-15 18:54:53'),(908,10,1,'buy 9 1/2\" x 2\' rebar','',1,26,0,0,'2008-07-17','2008-07-27','Done','','2009-05-15 18:54:53'),(1624,10,1,'check everything off list','',1,26,0,0,'2010-07-27','2010-08-08','Done',NULL,'2010-08-09 00:43:54'),(1623,4,1,'other cloth