INSERT INTO `todolist2` VALUES (1,0,1,'Allow editing','Change each list entry so that it is an editable field and then catch the result and update it. ',1,6,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(2,30,1,'add code to select only one product','perhaps pass into lister a ?product=\"\" field and parse that out; allow for \"all\"\r\nMaybe when it\'s all we don\'t sort on product? \r\n\r\nI\'m thinking that we still start without this but at the top of the page we have a pull down with a list of products that links back to todo with the right product set in the url. Should work \r\n\r\nOh, here\'s a simple fix: make the name of the product a link to the list of only that product. Add a link at the top for \"all products\" (possibly suppress this link when you are already on all products\"). \r\n\r\n',1,6,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(3,101,1,'auto sequence','When you\'re adding items it might be nice to add them to the highest list of the product, or at least tell you what the highest list is\r\n\r\nMaybe the thing is that you can click a button and have it number all the items by 5. \r\n',1,6,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(93,0,1,'Add password protection under the new application system','\r\n',1,9,0,0,'2007-09-10 05:55:35'),(11,0,1,'Change done from number to letter','should by Y/N\r\n\r\nCome to think of it, do you really need the done field given that these are all undone?',1,6,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(12,90,1,'add a pulldown for the product list','We need a list of permitted products and a pulldown\r\nmaybe you can either enter one from the pulldown or enter a new one\r\n',1,6,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(13,110,1,'sensible password protection','A login.php that sets a cookie; add and list check and if the cookie isn\'t there you\'re out; the cookie lasts for a long time (month?); cookie is checked against list of valid users: user/pass is all that\'s there.',1,6,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(571,10,1,'verification function','The idea is to have a regular expression and a name in a database. like \"phone number\" and a regex that checks to make sure it\'s a phone number or \"email\" and regex that checks for that.\r\nThen you have another database that has a name (or, actually, a number) that relates to the regex and a field name. Finally, we have a routine. The routine runs through the list of $PARAMS and checks them against the database of field names, creating a list of errors. Basically, we call that at the top of every program. \r\n\r\nA potential problem is the name space. One program\'s \"name\" may require a different regex than another program\'s name. But we want to be able to reuse field names and their regex (which means that for most programs you\'ll only have to actually write one or two regex\'s and get the rest of the verification system for free). \r\n\r\n',0,5,0,0,'2007-09-19 15:06:51'),(569,15,1,'Consider linking todo and design','If we had todo get it\'s project name from the design data base and then linked over there to create new projects the two would be loosely bound. ',0,6,0,0,'2007-09-20 21:17:54'),(567,10,1,'make html more css compatable','',0,5,0,0,'2007-09-19 14:58:19'),(568,12,1,'make it possible to have multiple users for todo','This means that we\'ll have a field in the list (and on the project list, too) that has a user number. Users can only see their own, admins can see everything. \r\n\r\n',1,6,0,0,'2007-10-07 04:14:40'),(20,0,1,'You don\'t need a \"Done\" field when you enter an item','Items that you are entering are new and so, logically, can\'t be done. Therefore the done field should be removed.',1,6,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(21,0,1,'in listing, there should be a \"done\" checkbox','',1,6,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(22,0,1,'Lord, I need an editor for these todos!','Now I have duplicates, items out of order, bad descriptions; it\'s a mess!',1,6,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(566,5,1,'change keith@menconi.com to kmenconi89@yahoo.com','\r\n',0,9,0,0,'2008-03-15 19:11:02'),(562,0,1,'talk to Joe about drum le