rmal design. Comments can have just a link or maybe a pulldown menu with an entry for each comment. \r\nMaybe comments to formal documents should be to the whole document. Keeping track of which deail module design this comment is for is a bit difficult. And I\'m not sure it\'s fair to the author to have tons of comments on each section. on the other hand, commenting on each section makes it easier to be specific in the comments and, in some ways, makes it easier to take them into account. \r\nComments on a specific module should be shown on the edit page for that module. ',1,20,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(156,0,1,'use new first order normalization privs','The system currently works on a priv list. It should work on a table that has a record for each priv/user combo. Write a routine that will fetch an array of privs and pass that back. Then look the priv up in there. ',1,14,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(157,1,1,'switch to one cookie system','We want to have one cookie that authenticates a user and then have each application get a list of privs for that user and see if he\'s authorized. \r\n\r\nThis is cleaner, requires only one login and prevents us having dozens of cookies on a system. ',1,14,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(158,3,1,'Add user and application management pages','Currently you have to log in to the DB to manage the login system; add a program that does the management. ',1,14,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(159,4,1,'Use HTTPS for login stuff','It may just work!',1,14,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(160,1,1,'An overall todo list would be very helpful','Perhaps if each application had a sequence number and the overall list added item and product numbers together and sorted on that. ',1,6,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(161,0,1,'reinstall kyocera handheld disk','\r\n',1,9,0,0,'2007-09-10 05:55:35'),(170,0,1,'Add $Log $ and $Id$ to bigloser files','Add $Log $ and $Id$ to bigloser files\r\n/*\r\n * $Log$\r\n */ \r\nat the end\r\n/* $Id$ */ at the start\r\nconsider \r\n$rcsversion=$Id$;\r\n ',1,15,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(171,0,1,'Add $Log $ and $Id$ to bigloser files','\r\n/*\r\n * $Log$\r\n */ \r\nat the end\r\n/* $Id$ */ at the start\r\nconsider \r\n$rcsversion=$Id$;',1,4,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(172,0,1,'Add $Log $ and $Id$ to bigloser files','Add $Log $ and $Id$ to bigloser files\r\n/*\r\n * $Log$\r\n */ \r\nat the end\r\n/* $Id$ */ at the start\r\nconsider \r\n$rcsversion=$Id$;\r\n ',1,14,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(173,0,1,'Add $Log $ and $Id$ to bigloser files','Add $Log $ and $Id$ to bigloser files\r\n/*\r\n * $Log$\r\n */ \r\nat the end\r\n/* $Id$ */ at the start\r\nconsider \r\n$rcsversion=$Id$;\r\n ',1,20,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(178,0,1,'add a link on directory for adding new designs','index?mode=newdesign\r\n',1,20,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(179,1,1,'add the form to edit formal designs','http://67.113.154.163/designs/index.php?mode=formaledit&designno=1\r\nFirst it has a list of the sections, each with a check box for deleting it. (that\'s the first form, button at the bottom of the list \"delete sections\")\r\nEach section name is a link to the element in the form that\'s the textarea for that section\r\nThen it has a short form for adding new sections. That\'s the second form.\r\nThen it has a fomr with each section, title followed by textarea, with a button at the bottom that says \"update sections\". \r\nThen it has a list of modules, just like sections, with links to text areas and so forth. ',1,20,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(180,20,1,'add dates to done items, show when it was entered and when completed','',1,6,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(181,21,1,'add a report  on done items','now that we have start and end dates, how about a report that lists all the done items how long they took. How many items we finished each month, each year and so on. ',1,6,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(182,1,1,'add code to use the new version functions','Add code to call the version functions\r\nMaybe even put at the head of every file\r\ndebug_string(\"foo version\",foo_version()); \r\nso that when debug is on it displays the version of everything. Maybe annoying verbose but quite possibly useful at some point.',1,5,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(183,1,1,'In the MYSQL functions, add the new code from whatchamall','Whatchamall has code for doing simple and complicated selects which shouild be added. ',1,5,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(184,1,1,'add a \"game score list\" for how many different parties each game has been played','\r\nselect gamesname,eventid,eventdate, count(game) as count from events,games where game=gameid group by eventdate,gamesname order by gamesname;\r\n\r\nThis gives a list of games we such that each game appears not more than once per party. SO the number of times each game appears in this list is it\'s \"score\" such that it gets no extra points for being played more than once in a games party. Thus Zendo would get a score of 1 not 3 and fluxx gets only 6 instead of 14.\r\n\r\nGet a list of all the game we have. Then step through each of them and do this select with the addition of a \"where game=$thisgame\" with $thisgame being one game from the list. The num rows is the score for the game. Obviously, we\'ll want to limit the scope of the query.\r\n',1,15,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(185,60,1,'Add a Game Party Review Page','How about a page that you select by selecting a date from a list and then it shows the games played and the players and the winners and losers (we already have code to do winners and losers). \r\n\r\nALSO, how about a list of pictures that relate to games and players and we randomly scatter them from among the set of pictures we have. \r\n\r\nThis gives the lsit of games\r\nselect gamesname,eventdate from events,games where gameid=game and eventdate=\'2005-02-12\';\r\n\r\nThis gives the list of players\r\nselect playername,eventdate from players, events,winlose where playerid=player and eventid=gameeventid and eventdate=\'2005-02-12\' group by playername;\r\n\r\nthis gives the eventdates\r\n select eventdate from  events group by eventdate;\r\n',1,15,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(461,20,1,'Group Scheduler Normalize the dates','We need a routine that can take a list of epoch numbers and make sure they all represent NOON, not some other value. For that, we want to convert the epoch to a list of numbers representing Day,month and year and then convert it back with a 12 in the hour position and 0s everywhere else. \r\n\r\nOther than this one thing, epoch is pretty good. A date format like this YYYYMMDD might be better because it will sort, it\'s unique but there are no \"false negatives\" (that is, two dates don\'t match because one is noon and one 1 PM  -- which can happen because of daylight savings time). Also Epoch time is a Unix thing. \r\n\r\n\r\n',0,33,0,0,'2007-09-05 22:28:17'),(460,20,1,'Group Scheduler: routine to count misses','The core routine for Meeting maker is a routine that takes a list of dates from each participant and returns a list of dates with counts. It\'s important that it also have the first and last date. \r\nThe requires that it find all the dates in the range, create an array with those dates as keys and then root through all the dates and count them all up. \r\n\r\n',0,33,0,0,'2007-09-05 22:27:02'),(459,20,1,'Group Scheduler: date list inverter','I have a routine that gets a list of all the dates between two dates. I need a routine, that, given a list of dates and a start and end date, will give you a list of dates not on the list. \r\n\r\n\r\n',0,33,0,0,'2007-09-05 22:27:09'),(458,12,1,'Make the meditation list a generic function','Currently the meditation list takes a data array and makes it a multi-column table. That\'s good. But if it only worked out the headers on it\'s own, it would be generic and we could use it generally.\r\n\r\nGet the keys for the headers (php/array.php). Also allow the user to provide a set of headers in a assoc array. \r\n',0,5,0,0,'2007-09-10 06:01:41'),(190,0,1,'add the code from debug to the library routine','I added a number of improvements, from fixing the log flag name to checking to make sure there is actually elements in a array before we display it to returning the value of a flag when you change it. All this should be saved to the general routines.',1,5,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(455,20,1,'Group Scheduler: What else is missing?','\r\n\r\n\r\n',0,33,0,0,'2007-11-17 19:22:34'),(457,10,1,'fix login','The login page is \"upside down\" when there\'s not registration. It\'s fairly obvious that it\'s because of a mal-formed table (that all seemed too easy).\r\nThe table doesn\'t have a </table> -- that\'s the whole problem!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',0,14,0,0,'2007-11-17 19:19:11'),(192,4,1,'Generalize Modules to \"subsections\"','The concept of a subsection is that any section can have \"subsubsection\". There is a place to add subsections and you edit those subsections. Then, in the final document, the subsections are show like the modules and case studies are shown.\r\n\r\nThere should be a check box on the edit formal page. Plus a form at the bottom to add subsections (which may be the one to add sections, modified). \r\n',1,20,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(193,0,1,'Add a form to add sections','THis form is at the bottom of the \"edit formal\" page. It allows you to specify the title of a new section and whether this has subsections or not. It is assumed that the design this goes to is the current design. ',1,20,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(194,1,1,'add the ability to edit the titles and subsection status of sections','Currently you can\'t edit the title and can\'t change whether the section has subsections. ',1,20,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(195,3,1,'Add a link to each design on the directory page to edit the design','You need to be able to edit things about a design such as author, name, description and so forth. ',1,20,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(196,5,1,'Add a link to every section with subsections that allows you to add the subsection','Not sure exactly how this works. One way is to add a link to each section that has subsections that takes you to another page where you enter the data. \r\n\r\nAnother possibility is to simply have it add a totally blank subsection which you then fill in when the page redraws (I imagine that the subsection will be part of the form but indented under their sections so adding a subsection will cause another set of fields to appear under the section which you can then fill in whenever. )\r\n\r\nA third possibility is to add a subsection the same way you add a section: you just add a section and specify that it\'s a subsection and which section it belongs to (with a pulldown). This could be an addition to the \"add a section\" form (just add a pulldown \"notsubsection\" plus a list of all the possible sections a subsection could belong to).\r\n\r\nA fourth possibility is that there is, in addition to an add section form, an add subsection form. I think I like this a little better than 3 because 3 is confusing and can have conflicts (what if I check \"this section has subsections\"  AND select a section that it belongs to -- I\'m sure not going to allow a hierarchy). \r\n',1,20,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(197,0,1,'Get New Phone','',1,9,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(198,4,1,'enter new board minutes','ENter them, distribute them, print them, etc',1,9,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(199,55,1,'find board minutes at church','Find them, check to see how up to date they are, etc',1,9,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(200,23,1,'subscribe to upladder','Subscribe to premium upladder and see what they can do for us',1,9,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(201,20,1,'craigs list','go to craigs list and get job listings -- maybe it\'s improved\r\nalso, why not put a resume on there',1,9,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(202,30,1,'job list survey','Do a survey of job listings and see if any thing has changed',1,9,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(203,90,1,'sbsma','goto joe\'s address and start working on 