a database of words','I was thinking it could have the word, the primary type (noun, verb, adverb, adjective, etc) and a bool for each of these which is set to yes if it can be -- USED that way. Plus a count. \r\n\r\nThen we open a specified file full of words, parse out the actual words and dump them into an array. Each array has a word as an index and a count as the value. As we add words to the array we increment the count. \r\n\r\nWe get the database out and add the words from the one to the other, being careful to add the counts. \r\n\r\nThere is a routine that displays big hunks of words that allows me to set, by hand, the various parameters. ',0,22,0,0,'2008-04-13 18:37:36'),(225,100,1,'create a living will','What I want is a document that specifies that, should I be in a coma the decision to continue life support should be made by (in order of availability) you, Earl and (in some order) my mother, my kids, and other people I know and trust. Perhaps, you, Earl, Janine, Keith, mom, Dave Rossum, Ken Goodreau. \r\n\r\nThen I\'d add a non-binding document that expressed my opinions about how the decision should be made, were I to have anything to do with it. \r\n\r\nPrinciples\r\n1) I am not my body nor my mind. I am a creature of light. Therefor, once the spark is gone, what you do with shell is of no consequence to me.\r\n2) When I am gone, I am no longer concerned with the affairs of Men. I therefore do not get a vote.\r\n3) Choices must be made in the moment. Therefore, nothing I say or suggest in advance can have any real relevance to what is going on later. As a practical and legal matter, however, I need to specify who will make the choice in the moment on my behalf if I\'m not around to do it. Once that person is chosen, however, they have total control and should not be second guessed based on my comments (real or imagined) or my writings nor by any other communications beforehand. In The Moment.\r\n\r\nGuidelines\r\nAlthough the designated person has all the power, it\'s an aweful position to put someone in. ',1,9,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(226,5,1,'email about insurance','we want to change to kaiser; find out how to do that and send email',1,9,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(227,0,1,'get a car','find a car for keith',1,9,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(228,15,1,'find a painter','contact a painter and set up a meeting',1,9,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(229,15,1,'get car maintained','',1,9,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(230,1,1,'car wash','',1,9,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(231,8,1,'make the description column shorter on the notes','The right hand side of the page is squished a bit because the descriptions are too wide. Constrain the descriptions and it will look good again...',1,20,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(443,25,1,'Revisit Company List','Should we kill it or keep it?',0,9,0,0,'2007-09-10 05:55:35'),(444,25,1,'Revisit Redwall Game registry: Keep or Kill','WE should retire this as a good idea gone bad but don\'t retire the code.\r\n',0,8,0,0,'2007-09-05 22:27:27'),(441,20,1,'Fix design app so we have a notes link on the left','',1,9,0,0,'2007-09-10 05:55:35'),(439,20,1,'Fix mediation list','I want 5 separate lists instead of 8 columns',1,9,0,0,'2007-09-10 05:55:35'),(440,4,1,'Turnstyle: Add the numbers game pages','The numbers game gets it\'s own page with links to instance pages. \r\n\r\nThe important issue here is where we draw the line between public views and players. In the case of the numbers game the only thing that\'s really private is the users guess and that the user\'s personal history. If we made those two sections conditional we could show the same page for public and private -- but is that in line with Turnstyle?\r\n\r\nGame instances:\r\npast (complete) present (running)  and future (starting) games \r\nWe show this with starting games at the top, present games in the middle and past games running off the edge. \r\nthere are potentially signup,  game (orders) pages and rail (non-player, public) pages\r\n\r\nfor past games there are rail pages that show the status of the game at the end (this might be special in that we\'ll show the winners)\r\n\r\n\r\ndefine things somewhere on the page (the meaning of \"game\" \"rail\" and \"signup\" -- maybe \"player\" \"public\" and \"signup\" or \"join\")\r\n',1,9,0,0,'2007-09-10 05:55:35'),(437,0,1,'BigLoser: Fix Wins on','\r\n',1,9,0,0,'2007-09-10 05:55:35'),(438,1,1,'Turnstyle: Create Front Page','We\'ve already writtend down what this should look like. Let\'s do it. WE have 2 Numbers Games, we can link them from there. \r\n\r\nNeed to add a GAMES table and an INSTANCE table and read the information from there. \r\n\r\nAlso need a \"news\" table and read that in, too.\r\n\r\n',1,9,0,0,'2007-09-10 05:55:35'),(241,0,1,'upgrade all library routines from the whatchamall stuff','Most of them have new things but you can\'t just copy it over',1,5,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(242,99,1,'Move finished apps to menconi.com','Move the following: \r\nTodo\r\nBigloser\r\ndesigns\r\n TO menconi.com. THe versions on the brain can remain as the development version but the live version should be on menconi.com\r\n',1,9,0,0,'2007-09-10 05:55:35'),(243,10,1,'add drive to menconi.com','It really needs a bigger drive, I have a bigger drive and this is more important that other things.',1,9,0,0,'2007-09-10 05:55:35'),(244,1,1,'Add a simple priority to todo list items','Add a priority of    \"very low\",\"low\",\"normal\", \"high\",\"urgent\",\"immediate\"  or 1-5 or some other paradigm to each item on the todo list. Then add a pulldown on the display that hides everything below a certain level. \r\n\r\nObvioiusly, you have to be able to set and edit the priority later.\r\n\r\nThat will go a long way to improving the usefulness of the list!',1,6,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(245,0,1,'add addresses to church site','',1,9,0,0,'2007-09-10 05:55:35'),(246,0,1,'learn the commands for cvs','Just going to have to bite the bullet and learn this stuff.',1,9,0,0,'2007-09-10 05:55:35'),(247,20,1,'work out a procedure for updating applications','Look, we have \"finished\" applications on menconi.com and we\'ve made changes to them on thebrain. What procedure do we use to move them over? \r\n\r\nFirst off, we need to get the databases aligned so I can use the version on thebrain to test it but not make it live. \r\n\r\nThen we use that one for a month and then move the code to the live system. ',1,9,0,0,'2007-09-10 05:55:35'),(248,0,1,'fix the linux network','Date: Mon, 18 Jul 2005 17:00:48 -0700\r\nTo: scott@spamwolf.com\r\nFrom: Dave <reply@menconi.com>\r\nSubject: Help With My Linux Box\r\n\r\nI\'m still having trouble with my network connections (you helped me with them some months back and said that it would be find if I sent you email if I had further problems). I\'ve been poking at it to try to get a good lock on the problems I DO have.\r\n\r\nThere are 2 (major) problems. The first is that the system doesn\'t work when it boots up. I have to type\r\nbash /etc/rc.local\r\nas root before I can connect to the box. rc.local is\r\n[root@localhost root]# cat /etc/rc.local\r\n#!/bin/sh\r\n#\r\n# This script will be executed *after* all the other init scripts.\r\n# You can put your own initialization stuff in here if you don\'t\r\n# want to do the full Sys V style init stuff.\r\n\r\ntouch /var/lock/subsys/local\r\n/sbin/route del default gw 192.168.1.1\r\n/sbin/route add default gw 192.168.2.1\r\n\r\n[root@localhost root]#\r\nI think we have this fixed (mostly) but it\'s not running at startup.\r\n\r\nHere\'s how my network works:  192.168.1.1 is the gateway for the 67.113.154.162 address (and the wireless access point and my desktop). They all go through a firewall/router. The 162 box is menconi.com and also has a local address of 192.168.1.11.\r\n192.168.2.1 is the gateway for the 67.113.154.163 which is the box I\'m having trouble with. I call it \"thebrain\" but it doesn\'t really have domain name. It\'s also has a nic card connected to the 192.168.1.* network and has a fixed address on that network of 192.168.1.12. \r\n\r\nMy second problem is that thebrain won\'t accept co[root@localhost root]# cat /etc/rc.local\r\n#!/bin/sh\r\n#\r\n# This script will be executed *after* all the other init scripts.\r\n# You can put your own initialization stuff in here if you don\'t\r\n# want to do the full Sys V style init stuff.\r\n\r\ntouch /var/lock/subsys/local\r\n/sbin/route del default gw 192.168.1.1\r\n/sbin/route add default gw 192.168.2.1\r\n\r\n[root@localhost root]#\r\n\r\n\r\nHere\'s how my network works: \r\nThere is a 192.168.1.1 network which goes through a firewall/router and includes all the computers in the house (menconi.com, my desktop, and the wireless access point). Menconi.com is 67.113.154.162 because this router accepts anything addressed to that box and sends it to 192.168.1.11 which is the spiderman box. That seems to work perfectly.\r\n\r\nThere is also a 192.168.2.1 network which goes through a different firewall/router and includes only \"thebrain\" which has a Nat address of 192.168.2.12 and 192.168.1.12 (two nic cards) and an internet address of 67.113.154.163.\r\n\r\nSpiderman and the rest of the \"1\" network works fine.\r\n\r\nTheBrain can\'t be connected to at all until I run the /etc/rc.local file by hand and then it accepts connections from 67.113.154.163 (which means that it\'s active on the \"2\" network.\r\n\r\nThe 2nd problem is that it doesn\'t accept connections to 192.168.1.12. I get an error \"no route to host\". \r\n\r\nWhen I run ifconfig I get this: \r\n\r\n\r\n[root@localhost root]# ifconfig\r\neth0      Link encap:Ethernet  HWaddr 00:20:18:2A:57:D5\r\n          inet addr:192.168.2.12  Bcast:192.168.2.255  Mask:255.255.255.0\r\n          UP BROADCAST RUNNING MULTICAST  MTU:1500  Metric:1\r\n          RX packets:6681 errors:0 dropped:0 overruns:0 frame:0\r\n          TX packets:7084 errors:0 dropped:0 overruns:0 carrier:0\r\n          collisions:2 txqueuelen:100\r\n          RX bytes:565764 (552.5 Kb)  TX bytes:1151288 (1.0 Mb)\r\n          Interrupt:5 Base address:0xe800\r\n\r\neth1      Link encap:Ethernet  HWaddr 00:40:33:93:F2:49\r\n          inet addr:192.168.1.12  Bcast:192.168.1.255  Mask:255.255.255.0\r\n          UP BROADCAST RUNNING MULTICAST  MTU:1500  Metric:1\r\n          RX packets:0 errors:0 dropped:0 overruns:0 frame:0\r\n          TX packets:0 errors:2548 dropped:0 overruns:0 carrier:5096\r\n          collisions:43316 txqueuelen:100\r\n          RX bytes:0 (0.0 b)  TX bytes:152880 (149.2 Kb)\r\n          Interrupt:10 Base address:0xec00\r\n\r\nlo        Link encap:Local Loopback\r\n          inet addr:127.0.0.1  Mask:255.0.0.0\r\n          UP LOOPBACK RUNNING  MTU:16436  Metric:1\r\n          RX packets:733725 errors:0 dropped:0 overruns:0 frame:0\r\n          TX packets:733725 errors:0 dropped:0 overruns:0 carrier:0\r\n          collisions:0 txqueuelen:0\r\n          RX bytes:50128823 (47.8 Mb)  TX bytes:50128823 (47.8 Mb)\r\n\r\n[root@localhost root]#\r\n\r\n\r\nIt all looks OK but it doesn\'t work!\r\n\r\nPlease help!\r\n\r\nDave\r\n\r\n',1,9,0,0,'2007-09-10 05:55:35'),(249,0,1,'have login return a list of the users for a particular application','By passing the application word and appnum, an application can get the list of users who are allowed to access this application. The application can then use this information for role based security.',1,14,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(250,10,1,'Get the login admin working','',1,9,0,0,'2007-09-10 05:55:35'),(251,10,1,'add application user reporting to login','',1,9,0,0,'2007-09-10 05:55:35'),(252,5,1,'add design-based control of access to design','',1,9,0,0,'2007-09-10 05:55:35'),(253,1,1,'create the basic game registration system','',1,9,0,0,'2007-09-10 05:55:35'),(254,0,1,'Get the house painted','',1,9,0,0,'2007-09-10 05:55:35'),(255,50,1,'call overhead door','',1,9,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(256,7,1,'call etronics','',1,9,0,0,'2007-08-04 02:38:19'),(2